Acidic_Glands.description: A diseased specimen that can be cleaned to gain animal fat.  Toxic to humans, this will damage you when carried.

Advanced_Alteration_Bench.description: A bench with a 3d printer to create any attachment. Allows faster altering of items than the basic Alteration Bench.

Advanced_Aquarium.description: A very fancy fish tank for keeping your favourite finned friends around, must be connected to both power and water.
Advanced_Aquarium.flavorText: I repeat, do NOT tap on the glass.

Advanced_Armor_Bench.description: Craft and assemble advanced protective items and garments.
Advanced_Armor_Bench.flavorText: With the ability to weave platinum into fiber and cure leather on a drying rack prospectors can craft tougher outfits for the harsh environment of Icarus.

Advanced_Cloth_Arms.description: Light and breathable, designed for long journeys through the harsh sands of Icarus.

Advanced_Cloth_Chest.description: Light and breathable, designed for long journeys through the harsh sands of Icarus.

Advanced_Cloth_Feet.description: Light and breathable, designed for long journeys through the harsh sands of Icarus.

Advanced_Cloth_Head.description: Light and breathable, designed for long journeys through the harsh sands of Icarus.

Advanced_Cloth_Legs.description: Light and breathable, designed for long journeys through the harsh sands of Icarus.

Advanced_Fishing_Trap.description: An advanced trap that can catch all types of fish.

Advanced_Iron_Lure.description: A sophisticated lure carefully crafted out of iron, to attract more fish.
Advanced_Iron_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Advanced_Kitchen_Bench.flavorText: Cleaner and more durable than other benches on Icarus.

Advanced_Kitchen_Sink.description: Fully plumbed basin and running water, a luxury of sorts.

Advanced_Kitchen_Storage.description: The best cabinets this planet can offer.

Advanced_Leather.description: Treated leather for a more durable prospector protection solution.

Advanced_Leather_Process.description: Treated leather in the process of drying.
Advanced_Leather_Process.flavorText: Given time this leather will be able to be put to good use.

AlienFossil_Conch.description: A decorated conch shell etched with strange markings.

AlienFossil_Pottery.description: An oddly-marked clay vessel, that has been damaged by something.

Alpha_Sandworm_Statue_Bronze.description: A Sandworm in all its bronzed glory.
Alpha_Sandworm_Statue_Bronze.flavorText: It doesnt look too tough, at this size...

Alphawolf_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Alpha Wolf.
Alphawolf_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Alphawolf_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Alteration_Bench.description: A bench with built-in drill press for crafting attachments and a workspace for altering Items.

Aluminium.description: A lightweight and easily milled ingot of aluminium.
Aluminium.flavorText: I dont have aluminium foil on my windows any more. - Rick James

Aluminium_Arrow.description: A mid-grade, lightweight arrow giving decent range and damage.

Ammo_Casing.description: A rough iron ammo casing that can be used to create all types of ammo.
Ammo_Casing.flavorText: Basic building blocks for firearm ammunition.

Ammo_Pistol_Round_Armor_Piercing.description: 9mm ammunition which can pierce the toughest surfaces.

Ammo_Pistol_Round_Cold_Steel.description: A sturdy round crafted using Cold Steel, unique to Icarus.
Ammo_Pistol_Round_Cold_Steel.flavorText: One of the few items that are only available on Icarus, due to the nature of the materials required.

Ammo_Pistol_Round_Incendiary.description: 9mm ammunition which can ignite flammable targets.

Ammo_Pistol_Round_Iron_Wood.description: A toxin-coated round, carefully crafted using Miasma harvested from Icarus wildlife.
Ammo_Pistol_Round_Iron_Wood.flavorText: The miasma coating this tool emits an almost unbearable stench.

Ammo_Pistol_Round_Obsidian.description: A lightweight round created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Ammo_Pistol_Round_Obsidian.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Ammo_Rifle_Round_Armor_Piercing.description: 7.62mm ammunition which can pierce the toughest surfaces

Ammo_Rifle_Round_Cold_Steel.description: A sturdy round crafted using Cold Steel, unique to Icarus.
Ammo_Rifle_Round_Cold_Steel.flavorText: One of the few items that are only available on Icarus, due to the nature of the materials required.

Ammo_Rifle_Round_Incendiary.description: 7.62mm ammunition which can ignite flammable targets.

Ammo_Rifle_Round_Iron_Wood.description: A toxin-coated round, carefully crafted using Miasma harvested from Icarus wildlife.
Ammo_Rifle_Round_Iron_Wood.flavorText: The miasma coating this tool emits an almost unbearable stench.

Ammo_Rifle_Round_Obsidian.description: A lightweight round created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Ammo_Rifle_Round_Obsidian.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Ammo_Shell_ColdSteel.description: This deadly shotgun ammunition is cast in Cold Steel, giving you an edge in the wilderness of Icarus.
Ammo_Shell_ColdSteel.flavorText: On Icarus, you need every advantage you can get.

Ammo_Shell_Ironwood.description: This deadly shotgun ammunition is coated in a Miasmic film, giving you an edge in the wilderness of Icarus.
Ammo_Shell_Ironwood.flavorText: On Icarus, you need every advantage you can get.

Ammo_Shell_Obsidian.description: This deadly shotgun ammunition is crafted from Obsidian, giving you an edge in the wilderness of Icarus.
Ammo_Shell_Obsidian.flavorText: On Icarus, you need every advantage you can get.

AnimalCarcass_Alpha_Desert_Wolf.flavorText: The Formidable Alpha wolf variant endures where little else survives.

AnimalCarcass_Alpha_Snow_Wolf.flavorText: The Formidable Alpha wolf variant endures where little else survives.

AnimalCarcass_Alpha_Wolf.flavorText: The Formidable Alpha wolf variant endures where little else survives.

AnimalCarcass_BabyDeer.description: Far from Earth, further from help.
AnimalCarcass_BabyDeer.flavorText: Lightyears from Earth, the corpse of a baby deer somehow retains an echo of the tragic.

AnimalCarcass_BatDog.description: A hideous mutant now at peace.
AnimalCarcass_BatDog.flavorText: Though sympathy cant alter facts, it can help to make them more bearable. This creature deserves sympathy.

AnimalCarcass_Bear.flavorText: Within the zone of failed terraforming, little can challenge the grizzly variant as an apex predator. Outside the zone, however, is another matter.

AnimalCarcass_BearCub.flavorText: Youd better hope mumma bear isnt around.

AnimalCarcass_Bear_Contaminated.description: Poor creature seems to be contaminated by some toxin.
AnimalCarcass_Bear_Contaminated.flavorText: Within the zone of failed terraforming, little can challenge the grizzly variant as an apex predator. Outside the zone, however, is another matter.

AnimalCarcass_BlueBack.description: What the Blueback lacks in speed, it makes up for in bulk.

AnimalCarcass_BlueBack_Lava.description: The corpse of a sometimes gentle giant.

AnimalCarcass_Blueback_Lava_Mount.description: The corpse of a sometimes gentle giant.

AnimalCarcass_Blueback_Mount.description: What the Blueback lacks in speed, it makes up for in bulk.

AnimalCarcass_Blueback_Mount_Daisy.description: The decaying remains of the Blueback known as Daisy

AnimalCarcass_Broodling.description: The spawn of a much larger creature.
AnimalCarcass_Broodling.flavorText: You really dont want to meet its parents.

AnimalCarcass_Broodling_WorldSpawn.description: The spawn of a much larger creature.
AnimalCarcass_Broodling_WorldSpawn.flavorText: You really dont want to meet its parents.

AnimalCarcass_Buffalo_Juvenile.description: A juvenile Buffalo which never quite made it to full adulthood.

AnimalCarcass_Chamois_M.description: A tough, fleet-footed variant of Earths goat-antelope.
AnimalCarcass_Chamois_M.flavorText: Terraforming failed, leaving a wasteland at ground zero, into which Earth-like forests and their natural inhabitants spread rapidly and easily.

AnimalCarcass_Chamois_Var.description: Similar to a Chamois. This animal shows signs of subtle mutation.
AnimalCarcass_Chamois_Var.flavorText: Engineered from the Capra family of goats on Earth. Known to be less graceful than their Earth counterparts.

AnimalCarcass_Conifer_Wolf.flavorText: A genetic variant of the grey wolf, this efficient carnivore is an indiscriminate hunter, thriving in the transplanted forests of Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Cougar_Alpha.description: The second most dangerous thing in the desert.
AnimalCarcass_Cougar_Alpha.flavorText: Introduced to manage the population of smaller mammals, the lion variant adopted swiftly to the arid regions of the new Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Crocodile.flavorText: From the prehistoric to today, prospectors will be dealing with these for a long time.

AnimalCarcass_Deer.description: A genetically modified member of the cervid family.
AnimalCarcass_Deer.flavorText: Modification of their respiratory system allows these deer variants to withstand - and thrive - despite Icaruss toxic atmosphere. Resources can be harvested by hand, but a skinning bench yields greater resources.

AnimalCarcass_DeerDesert.description: Imported from Earth, adjusted and released to the reformed deserts of Icarus.
AnimalCarcass_DeerDesert.flavorText: A hunter who is going to shoot an antelope does not waste his bullets on the dog. - Israelmore Ayivor

AnimalCarcass_DeerDesertLarge.flavorText: Further from the savannah than anyone ever expected.

AnimalCarcass_DeerLarge.description: A genetically modified member of the cervid family.
AnimalCarcass_DeerLarge.flavorText: Modification of their respiratory system allows these deer variants to withstand - and thrive - despite Icaruss toxic atmosphere.

AnimalCarcass_Deer_Variant.description: Muscular corpse of a deer-like creature.
AnimalCarcass_Deer_Variant.flavorText: Icarus is a microcosm of evolutionary extremes. Such pressures cause somewhat rapid and acute adaptation. The Equix for example, has twice the musculature at roughly twice the density compared to Earth cervidae.

AnimalCarcass_Desert_Striker.description: Fringe Zone apex predator, native to Icarus.
AnimalCarcass_Desert_Striker.flavorText: The most frightening predator found on Icarus, known for its intelligence. Stalkers are known to follow prospectors for hours, even days.

AnimalCarcass_Desert_Wolf.flavorText: Ever adaptable, the hyena endures where little else survives.

AnimalCarcass_Elephant.description: Near extinct on Earth, enduring on Icarus.
AnimalCarcass_Elephant.flavorText: Almost vanished on Earth, the Indian elephant was brought to Icarus to improve its chances of survival.

AnimalCarcass_Horse.description: A once powerful steed now lies cold at your feet.
AnimalCarcass_Horse.flavorText: The result of mixing DNA from Wild Boar and Horses on earth, with a dash of exotics thrown into the mix.

AnimalCarcass_Horse_Mount.description: A once powerful steed now lies cold at your feet.
AnimalCarcass_Horse_Mount.flavorText: The result of mixing DNA from Wild Boar and Horses on earth, with a dash of exotics thrown into the mix.

AnimalCarcass_Jaguar.description: The second most dangerous thing in the forest
AnimalCarcass_Jaguar.flavorText: Introduced to manage the population of smaller mammals, the jaguar variant adopted swiftly to the arid regions of the new Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Jaguar_Black.flavorText: Introduced to manage the population of smaller mammals, the jaguar variant adopted swiftly to the arid regions of the new Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_JuvieHorse.description: A juvenile Terrenus which never quite made it to full adulthood.
AnimalCarcass_JuvieHorse.flavorText: The result of mixing DNA from Wild Boar and Horses on earth, with a dash of exotics thrown into the mix.

AnimalCarcass_Kea.flavorText: Once endangered on Earth, Icarus brings new life to this native bird.

AnimalCarcass_Komodo.flavorText: Probably safer than a live one.

AnimalCarcass_Lava_Komodo.flavorText: Probably safer than a live one.

AnimalCarcass_Lava_Slug.description: A once-great creature, now lays dead at your feet.
AnimalCarcass_Lava_Slug.flavorText: Watch out for the remaining slime...

AnimalCarcass_Lion_F.description: The second most dangerous thing in the desert.
AnimalCarcass_Lion_F.flavorText: Introduced to manage the population of smaller mammals, the lion variant adopted swiftly to the arid regions of the new Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Mammoth.flavorText: In the aftermath of failed terraforming, this mammoth variant was released illicitly by a disillusioned geneticist. It found an unexpected home in the newly arctified snowfields of Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Moa.description: A once-extinct large predatory bird, native to New Zealand, brought back to life on Icarus through the terraforming process. And then killed again, by you.
AnimalCarcass_Moa.flavorText: At its peak, reaching almost 12 feet tall and over 500 pounds, this long neck means business.

AnimalCarcass_Moa_Juvenile.description: A juvenile Moa which never quite made it to full adulthood.

AnimalCarcass_Moa_Mount.description: A once-extinct large predatory bird, native to New Zealand, brought back to life on Icarus through the terraforming process. And then killed again, by you.
AnimalCarcass_Moa_Mount.flavorText: At its peak, reaching almost 12 feet tall and over 500 pounds, this long neck means business.

AnimalCarcass_Needler.flavorText: Bone-like spines push through the scales of this mutated reptile. This animal led a pain filled existence.

AnimalCarcass_Pack_Wolf.flavorText: A hyper-aggressive member of a genetically-altered wolf pack

AnimalCarcass_PolarBear.description: Emperor of the ice, highly aggressive.
AnimalCarcass_PolarBear.flavorText: After the Climate Emergency on Earth, the polar bear was approaching extinction. On Icarus, its variant has found a home on the planets newly-formed artic zones.

AnimalCarcass_PolarBearCub.description: Highly agressive, protected by the emperor of the arctic.
AnimalCarcass_PolarBearCub.flavorText: As an apex predator these polar bear cubs face little threat, except from you.

AnimalCarcass_PredatorBird.description: An endemic ambush predator torn from the skies.
AnimalCarcass_PredatorBird.flavorText: These intelligent flying reptiles are particular about their hunting opportunities. Often choosing targets that are weak or unaware. Mostly found scavenging an easy meal from a recent corpse.

AnimalCarcass_Pronghorn.description: A herd animal, able to endure the extremes of Icaruss environment.
AnimalCarcass_Pronghorn.flavorText: The pronghorn variant thrives on the sparse, desert terrain in which this region of Icarus now abounds.

AnimalCarcass_Rabbit.description: As on Earth, a survivor, but not today.
AnimalCarcass_Rabbit.flavorText: The rabbit variant has found a new niche on this malformed environment.

AnimalCarcass_Rabbit_Variant.description: As on Earth, a survivor, but not today.
AnimalCarcass_Rabbit_Variant.flavorText: The rabbit variant has found a new niche on this malformed environment.

AnimalCarcass_Raccoon.description: As on Earth, a survivor, but not today
AnimalCarcass_Raccoon.flavorText: The raccoon strain has found a new niche on this malformed environment.

AnimalCarcass_RedGoat.description: A natural survivor, thrives in arid climates.
AnimalCarcass_RedGoat.flavorText: One of the most successful transplants from Earth, the hardy red goat variant thrives on its adopted home.

AnimalCarcass_Roat.description: A dead specimen of local wildlife.
AnimalCarcass_Roat.flavorText: One of the rare endemic lifeforms able to survive in the failed terraforming zone, the roat endured the savage shift in Icaruss climate, due to its uniquely flexible respiratory system.

AnimalCarcass_Roat_Swamp.description: A dead specimen of local wildlife.
AnimalCarcass_Roat_Swamp.flavorText: One of the rare endemic lifeforms able to survive in the failed terraforming zone, the roat endured the savage shift in Icaruss climate, due to its uniquely flexible respiratory system.

AnimalCarcass_RockDog.description: A large predator with a rock-like outer coating that protects it from most damage.
AnimalCarcass_RockDog.flavorText: Known amongst new prospectors simply as the Rockdog, this creature is quickly gaining a reputation for causing nightmares for contractors in the area.

AnimalCarcass_Scorpion.description: One of the most dangerous creatures in the desert
AnimalCarcass_Scorpion.flavorText: This smooth plating could still be useful

AnimalCarcass_Scorpion_Arctic.description: One of the most dangerous creatures in the arctic
AnimalCarcass_Scorpion_Arctic.flavorText: This smooth plating could still be useful

AnimalCarcass_Scorpion_Armored.description: One of the most dangerous creatures in the clad in thick projectile resistance carapace.
AnimalCarcass_Scorpion_Armored.flavorText: This smooth plating could still be useful

AnimalCarcass_SnowLeopard.description: An exotic, evasive predator of the ice.
AnimalCarcass_SnowLeopard.flavorText: We nod, grimace, and resume our paths to separate destinies and graves. - Peter Matthiessen, The Snow Leopard

AnimalCarcass_SnowLeopard_Alpha.description: An exotic, evasive predator of the ice.
AnimalCarcass_SnowLeopard_Alpha.flavorText: We nod, grimace, and resume our paths to separate destinies and graves. - Peter Matthiessen, The Snow Leopard

AnimalCarcass_Snow_Rabbit.description: As on Earth, a survivor, but not today.
AnimalCarcass_Snow_Rabbit.flavorText: As reproductively prodigious, even in the harshest environments of Icarus, as it was on earth.

AnimalCarcass_Snow_Striker.description: Fringe Zone apex predator, native to Icarus.
AnimalCarcass_Snow_Striker.flavorText: The most frightening predator found on Icarus, known for its intelligence. Stalkers are known to follow prospectors for hours, even days.

AnimalCarcass_Snow_Striker_Mount.description: Fringe Zone apex predator, native to Icarus.
AnimalCarcass_Snow_Striker_Mount.flavorText: The most frightening predator found on Icarus, known for its intelligence. Stalkers are known to follow prospectors for hours, even days.

AnimalCarcass_Snow_Wolf.flavorText: Ever adaptable, the snow wolf variant endures where little else survives.

AnimalCarcass_SwampBird.description: The body of a large flightless bird. Its bone-like face makes a natural death mask.

AnimalCarcass_SwampQuad_Mount.description: The Stryder evolved to run. This one did not run fast enough.
AnimalCarcass_SwampQuad_Mount.flavorText: A snail, turtle and crab walked into a bar. Something obscene occurred, and we got the Stryder. Do you think it... tastes like crab?

AnimalCarcass_Swamp_Quad.description: The Stryder evolved to run. This one did not run fast enough.
AnimalCarcass_Swamp_Quad.flavorText: A snail, turtle and crab walked into a bar. Something obscene occurred, and we got the Stryder. Do you think it... tastes like crab?

AnimalCarcass_Swamp_Slug.description: Corpse of a giant slug, poisonous slime still drips off its lifeless body.

AnimalCarcass_Tusker.description: A once proud beast, now lies dead at your feet.

AnimalCarcass_Tusker_Juvenile.description: A juvenile Tusker which never quite made it to full adulthood.

AnimalCarcass_Tusker_Mount.description: A once proud beast, now lies dead at your feet.

AnimalCarcass_WildBoar.description: The remains of one of natures most feral creations.
AnimalCarcass_WildBoar.flavorText: Extraordinarily hardy and adaptable, this suid has become a wide-ranging pest in its short time on Icarus.

AnimalCarcass_Wooly_Zebra.description: A gregarious, migratory grazer and icon of the savannah.
AnimalCarcass_Wooly_Zebra.flavorText: The exact purpose of zebra stripes remains a mystery.

AnimalCarcass_Wulv.description: A relative of the wolf, altered by exposure to exotic matter.
AnimalCarcass_Wulv.flavorText: This relative of the wolf, has been genetically warped by sustained exposure to exotic matter, which is believed to reactivate sections of so-called junk DNA.

AnimalCarcass_Zebra.description: A gregarious, migratory grazer and icon of the savannah.
AnimalCarcass_Zebra.flavorText: The exact purpose of zebra stripes remains a mystery.

Animal_Bed.description: Juvenile animals can use this as a designated sleeping spot

Animal_Fat.description: The next best thing to butter.
Animal_Fat.flavorText: A key ingredient in energy dense cooking, life on any world would be almost unliveable without some kind of lipid.

Antibiotic_Paste.description: Reduces the effects of food poisoning, and other low grade infections.
Antibiotic_Paste.flavorText: A natural antibacterial agent that diminishes the impact of afflictions such as infected wounds and pnuemonia.

Antibiotic_Pill.description: A broad-spectrum antibacterial agent, protecting against food poisoning, wound infections and pneumonia.
Antibiotic_Pill.flavorText: While not quite invincible, your susceptibility to microbial takeover will temporarily reach an all-time low.

Antibiotic_Tonic.description: An antibacterial distillation that cures food poisoning, wound infections and afflictions like pneumonia.
Antibiotic_Tonic.flavorText: The interaction between bioactive substances and microbial life here on Icarus is still poorly understood, especially when one factors in the effects of exotic matter to both.

Antiparasitic_Item.description: A powerful medical preparation for curing festering wounds.
Antiparasitic_Item.flavorText: From suppurating wounds to dysentery, this natural broad-spectrum antibiotic remedy cures it all.

Antiparasitic_Paste.description: A medical preparation for reducing the effects of festering wounds.
Antiparasitic_Paste.flavorText: From the very first, newcomers to Icarus noted the medicinal and bioactive properties of Earth-type plants were significantly more intense.

Antiparasitic_Pill.description: A potent antibacterial preparation for preventing festering wounds.
Antiparasitic_Pill.flavorText: Flooding your body with antibiotics is a double-edged sword, but if it stops you needing to use the word festering to describe part of your body, its worth it.

Antiparasitic_Tonic.description: A medicinal preparation for curing festering wounds.
Antiparasitic_Tonic.flavorText: From suppurating wounds to dysentery, this natural broad-spectrum antibiotic remedy cures it all.

Antipoison_Item.description: A basic toxicology and anti-venom kit to combat poisoning.
Antipoison_Item.flavorText: Its speculated that exotics may suffuse much of the plant life in the terrazone, imparting bioactive properties, though exactly what these are, whether theyre safe, and exactly how it works ... at this stage, who knows?

Antipoison_Paste.description: A basic toxicology and anti-venom kit to reduce the effects of poisoning.
Antipoison_Paste.flavorText: Its speculated that exotics may suffuse much of the plant life in the terrazone, imparting bioactive properties, though exactly what these are, whether theyre safe, and exactly how it works ... at this stage, who knows?

Antipoison_Pill.description: An long-acting anti-venom to prevent poisoning.

Antipoison_Tonic.flavorText: Of the many ways to die on Icarus, poisoning is perhaps the least glorious.

Antiseptic_Paste.description: Heals food poisoning, infected wounds and bacterial infections like pneumonia.
Antiseptic_Paste.flavorText: Broad-spectrum, natural antibiotics that provide some ongoing protection against afflictions such as pnuemonia.

Anvil_Bench.description: Heavyweight work surface for iron and steel tools, using ingots smelted in their appropriate furnaces.
Anvil_Bench.flavorText: Arguably the simplest fabrication system known to humanity.

Anvil_Bench_T3.description: A versatile forge powered by coal for crafting various weapons and tools.
Anvil_Bench_T3.flavorText: Try to keep all digits away from the anvil...

Anvil_Bench_T4.description: An impressive foundry powered by electricity for crafting various higher quality weapons and tools.
Anvil_Bench_T4.flavorText: The UDA states that it has been at least seven days since the last accident using this piece of equipment...

Aquarium.description: A handy fish tank for keeping your favourite finned friends around, powered by biofuel.

Arctic_Rabbit_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Arctic_Scorpion_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Arctic Scorpion.
Arctic_Scorpion_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Arctic_Scorpion_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Armor_Bench.description: Craft and assemble various protective items and garments.
Armor_Bench.flavorText: Basic fabric, leatherwork and armorers tools allow you to fashion a range of clothing and protective wear from natural materials and fibres.

Arms_Attachment_Tool_Use_1.description: An attachment that reduces the stamina used for tool actions and the durability loss of tools.
Arms_Attachment_Tool_Use_1.flavorText: Can be equipped to hands armor at an Alteration Bench.

Arms_Attachment_Tool_Use_2.description: An attachment that greatly reduces the stamina used for tool actions and the durability loss of tools.
Arms_Attachment_Tool_Use_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to hands armor at an Alteration Bench.

Ashen_Drake_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Ashen Drake.
Ashen_Drake_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Ashen_Drake_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Avocado.description: A fruit with a creamy texture and nutty flavor, high in healthy fats.
Avocado.flavorText: These are commonly used in Mexican cuisine.

Axe_Attachment_Felling_Yield_1.description: An attachment that increases the yield of wood from felling trees.
Axe_Attachment_Felling_Yield_1.flavorText: Can be equipped to a valid axe at an Alteration Bench.

Axe_Attachment_Felling_Yield_2.description: An attachment that greatly increases the yield of wood from felling trees.
Axe_Attachment_Felling_Yield_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to a valid axe at an Alteration Bench.

Bandage_Basic.description: Cloth bandages to stem bleeding and heal minor wounds.
Bandage_Basic.flavorText: The healing wont start until the bleeding stops.

Bandage_Cooling.description: A bandage with a soothing balm to quickly lower temperatures

Bandage_Heat.description: Cloth bandages impregnated with a warming salve, for treating frostbite.

Bark_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted from bark, to attract more fish.
Bark_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Basic_Backpack.description: A tough leather backpack that increases inventory space, carry weight capacity and reduces the weight of ore.
Basic_Backpack.flavorText: Sol Berlinski, now Lagos Unit dispatcher on Ceres Station, claims the design of the quietly iconic prospectors basic backpack was taught to him personally by Mo Chou.

Basic_Bandolier.description: A wearable ammo store, reducing firearms weight and reload speed.

Basic_Ceiling_Light.description: A ceiling-mounted lamp, providing wide illumination, needing power.
Basic_Ceiling_Light.flavorText: We forgive children who are afraid of the dark. The tragedy is adults afraid of the light. - Plato

Basic_Ceiling_Light_Shroud.description: A handy ceiling light that gives off a cozy glow.

Basic_Ceiling_Spotlight.description: A handy spotlight that gives off a bright glow.

Basic_Fertilizer.description: Provides a small bonus to growth speed and crop yield
Basic_Fertilizer.flavorText: A simple way to increase your harvest

Basic_Fishing_Trap.description: A simple trap that can catch Basic Low Quality Fish

Basic_Oxite_Dissolver.description: A simple device for processing oxite into oxygen.
Basic_Oxite_Dissolver.flavorText: The oxidizer is a slow, unpowered device that uses mechanical pressure to crush oxite, then store the resulting oxygen. Once the balloon begins to fill, consume oxygen from it directly.

Basic_Quiver.description: Dedicated arrow storage, allowing faster reloading, swifter aiming and higher arrow speeds.

Basic_Wall_Light.description: A wall-mounted lamp, providing wide illumination, needing power.

Basic_Wall_Light_Shroud.description: A handy ceiling light that gives off a cozy glow.

Bauxite.description: Sedimentary bauxite with a high aluminium content.

Bean.description: Close to the perfect food source.
Bean.flavorText: The argument over whether soy produces milk or juice rages into the 22nd century.

Bear_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Bear.
Bear_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Bear_Trophy.flavorText: Until you step beyond the terrazone, few totems of survival speak louder than a grizzlys silent head.

Bed_Bedroll.description: Once placed in shelter, a bed can be set as a respawn location. Can also be used to sleep through the night.
Bed_Bedroll.flavorText: A bed is where the soul returns after a nights travelling ~ Russian folk saying

Bed_Interior_Wood.description: Once placed in shelter, a bed can be set as a respawn location. Can also be used to sleep through the night.
Bed_Interior_Wood.flavorText: A solidly made, simple place to rest and restore energy

Bed_Wood.description: Once placed in shelter, a bed can be set as a respawn location. Can also be used to sleep through the night.
Bed_Wood.flavorText: Rest, restore energy, respawn as required.

Beer.description: Proving you can brew beer from just about anything.
Beer.flavorText: Warms the body, soothes the soul, increases regeneration rates.

Berry.description: Berries will satisfy hunger, hydrate slightly, and extend endurance, but not for long.

Biofuel_Can_Meta.description: A makeshift fuel canister, that can hold biofuel, comes prefilled.

Building_RepairTool.description: Maintain or upgrade your structures against the wrath of Icarus.
Building_RepairTool.flavorText: Quickly beat dislodged planks back into place, or replace those planks with sturdier materials, a single hammer does it all!

Building_UpgradeTool.description: Improve your structures without tearing them down.
Building_UpgradeTool.flavorText: Allows you to replace an existing structural piece for an advanced version, if you have that item in your inventory. Hold R when holding the tool.

Campfire.description: A place to cook food and fend the cold away.
Campfire.flavorText: One of the simplest sources of heat available on Icarus, the campfire burns sticks and wood to cook basic foods. Toxins in the planets atmosphere do not interfere with combustion.

Canteen_Lightweight.description: A lightweight vessel for holding water, has a small thermal protection layer, to keep the water cold.

Carbon_Arms.description: High strength, lightweight graphene nano-lattice armor from Norex.
Carbon_Arms.flavorText: Focused on energy absorbance rather than outright hardness, the materials graphene multi-layered construction bleeds impact energy away almost instantly.

Carbon_Arrow.description: Strength and lightness combined in one hard-hitting package.

Carbon_Chest.description: High strength, lightweight graphene nano-lattice armor from Norex.
Carbon_Chest.flavorText: Two hundred times stronger than steel and extraordinarily conductive, the IO suits graphene weave allows it to dissipate energy with near-perfect efficiency.

Carbon_Feet.description: High strength, lightweight graphene nano-lattice armor from Norex.
Carbon_Feet.flavorText: Norex is a grey research venture between old world ACS companies Norsec and mining giant ExMin.

Carbon_Fiber.description: A lightweight, flexible construction material with high tensile strength.

Carbon_Head.description: High strength, lightweight graphene nano-lattice armor from Norex.
Carbon_Head.flavorText: A high-tech balance of physical protection, lightweight nano-construction, energy absorbance and protection against extremes of temperature.

Carbon_Legs.description: High strength, lightweight graphene nano-lattice armor from Norex.
Carbon_Legs.flavorText: A product of zero-g manufacturing techniques, this semi-rigid mid-weight graphene protextile is renowned for protecting against micro-meteorites travelling at upward of 10km/sec.

Carbon_Paste.description: A carbon-based admixture used in advanced constructions.

Carbon_Spear.description: A light, resilient spear made of layered carbon fiber.

Carbon_Throwing_Spear.description: A light, resilient spear made of layered carbon fiber.

Coconut_mature.description: Maturity diminishes liquid content, but offers more satisfying flesh.
Coconut_mature.flavorText: A coconuts final stage is also its most energy-rich.

Coconut_mid.description: A balance of light sustenance and moderate hydration, in a fibrous shell.
Coconut_mid.flavorText: Ripe coconuts contain a balance of thirst-quenching liquid and energy-dense, hunger satisfying flesh.

Coconut_young.description: Mostly water, young coconuts will quench thirst but wont do much for hunger.
Coconut_young.flavorText: Like sharks, coconuts often fail to live up to their lethal reputation.

Coffee.flavorText: Humanity was never going to last long in Icarus without it.

Cold_Steel_Arrow.flavorText: One of the few tools that are only available on Icarus, due to the nature of the materials required.

Composite_Legs.flavorText: Employing ultra-high molecular weight thermoplastics, composite armor trades weight for extraordinary protection against physical damage and exposure.

Composite_Spear.description: Low weight, high strength, extreme damage.
Composite_Spear.flavorText: Bringing two thousand years of materials technology to a sharp stick, the composite spear is lethal at long range or close quarters.

Composite_Throwing_Spear.description: Low weight, high strength, extreme damage.
Composite_Throwing_Spear.flavorText: Bringing two thousand years of materials technology to a sharp stick, the composite spear is lethal at long range or close quarters.

Composites.description: An extremely strong, light and endurant construction material.

Composter.description: Rapidly decomposes organic matter into biofuel, which is collected by adding a biofuel can. Can be connected to a water network for increased processing speed.
Composter.flavorText: Requires a fuel can to be added to collect biofuel.

Composter_Electric.description: Advanced biofuel unit for accelerated production.
Composter_Electric.flavorText: An upshot of the Climate Emergency was a focus on efficient, sustainable technology that squeezes every ounce of energy from nature.

Composter_Wood.description: Change your trash into Fertilizer with this simple composter. Items placed in this device will spoil at an accelerated rate.

Concrete_Beam.description: Anchors structures to the ground for extremely high building.
Concrete_Beam.flavorText: Beams connect vertically and diagonally to support multi-level construction. Your HUD will indicate when beams are anchored with a blue cursor. Increasing the quantity of beams at lower levels will increase build height even further.

Concrete_Floor.description: Strong and stable, a floor that endures the worst Icarus can deliver.

Concrete_Frame.description: The strongest, most stable foundation for any structure.

Concrete_Furnace_V2.description: An insulated, high-temperature furnace for smelting a wide range of materials including steel.
Concrete_Furnace_V2.flavorText: Icaruss oxygen levels may slow combustion, but ceramic insulation produces temperatures sufficient for smelting more advanced alloys.

Concrete_Half_Pitch.flavorText: A two part construction element, containing a base slope and an upper slope, for building low-pitched roofs.

Concrete_Halfpiece.description: Half- and quarter-sized building elements for detailed construction work.
Concrete_Halfpiece.flavorText: These sets are useful for creating walkways, balconies, trims and a range of other smaller constructions.

Concrete_Mix.description: A rudimentary, but serviceable concrete analogue.
Concrete_Mix.flavorText: Invented almost 8000 years ago, the composition of concrete has always varied depending on available resources and needs. Never was this more true than on Icarus.

Concrete_Ramp.description: A high strength slope for roofing, supports great weight.

Concrete_Roof_Corner.description: A strong insert for angled roofs.

Concrete_TrapDoor.flavorText: May be attached to a floorpiece with a trapdoor accessway.

Concrete_Wall_Angle.description: Moulded inserts for gables and other angular constructions..

Concrete_Window.description: A heavy duty, highly durable window.

Condensed_Enzymes.description: Condensed Enzymes Extracted from an Enzyme Geyser
Condensed_Enzymes.flavorText: Im sure there is a use for this.

ConiferWolf_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Wolf.
ConiferWolf_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

ConiferWolf_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Cooked_Bacon.description: A delicately thin slice of meat

Cooked_Carrot.flavorText: Boosts stamina slightly, may prompt angst.

Cooked_Corn.description: Grilled to perfection, depending on your standards.
Cooked_Corn.flavorText: A source of fuel for humans, animals and machines alike.

Cooked_Kumara.description: This meal has a caramelized exterior and soft and fluffy interior.
Cooked_Kumara.flavorText: Tastier than a staple food but just as easy.

Cooked_Meat.description: Can be eaten to satisfy hunger.
Cooked_Meat.flavorText: Cooked meat is easier to digest and provides more nutrition than raw flesh.

Cooked_Mushroom.flavorText: Mushrooms are notably the only lifeform introduced from Earth that required no genetic adjustment whatsoever.

Cooked_Potato.description: Improves stamina and keeps you fuller for longer.

Cooked_Prime_Meat.flavorText: Cooked meat is easier to digest and provides more nutrition than raw flesh.

Cooked_Pumpkin.flavorText: The pumpkins natural beta-carotene improves endurance.

Cooked_Rhubarb.description: This snack is lightly cooked in a pan with sugar or honey

Cooked_Squash.description: Like roast pumpkin, boasting a similar flavor and most of the same effects.
Cooked_Squash.flavorText: Boosts stamina, if not the will to live.

Cooked_Tomato.description: A hearty vegetable that improves health regeneration.

Cooking_Station_V2.description: A food preparation and butchering bench.
Cooking_Station_V2.flavorText: While it may not deliver high cuisine, the Cooking Station rewards the attentions of an attentive chef with a swifter, more sustaining food supply.

Cooler_Large.description: A powered heat exchange unit for cooling larger areas.

Copper_Bolt.description: Lightweight and strong, the copper bolt hits hard over distance.

Copper_Ore.description: Low grade copper ore, can be refined into pure ingots.
Copper_Ore.flavorText: The abundance of raw, high-quality metals on Icarus would have made it a goldmine, were it not so far removed from Earth.

Copper_Wire.description: This wire can be used in Electrical Circuits

Corn.flavorText: Cook or cultivate this ancient cereal, humanitys most widely produced grain.

Cougar_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Cougar.
Cougar_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Crafting_Bench.description: A sturdy construction bench, though useless without shelter.
Crafting_Bench.flavorText: A heavy woodworking table that enables construction of improved tools, weapons and structural elements.

Crocodile_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Crocodile.
Crocodile_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Crocodile_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Crossbow.description: Heavy hitting with a slow reload, so make it count.
Crossbow.flavorText: The first time I held a crossbow, I was confused. How can you feel powerful and so medieval at the same time? -- Anton Chang

Crumbed_Saltwater_Fillet.description: A crispy and savory dish made by coating tender fillets of fish in breadcrumbs and frying until golden brown.
Crumbed_Saltwater_Fillet.flavorText: Crispy on the outside, fishy on the inside.

Crushed_Bone.flavorText: Highly ground bone creates a useful ingredient for a range of concoctions.

Cured_Leather_Lure.description: A sophisticated lure carefully crafted out of leather, to attract more fish.
Cured_Leather_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

DEV_Pyromancy_Flame.description: Flame medium used by Great Swamp pyromancers. Pyromancers arouse this flame to produce various fire arts. Equip pyromancer flame to produce pyromancy

DebugViking.description: Meat from a recently killed animal, worth cooking first.
DebugViking.flavorText: Transplanted from Earth, a range of genetically modified animals thrive in the terrazone, providing an energy-dense food source.

Deep_Freeze.description: A freezer that preserves food but amasses ice very slowly and uses a fairly large amount of power.
Deep_Freeze.flavorText: Energy efficiency is important on EVERY planet.

Deep_Mining_Drill_Biofuel.description: A biofuel-powered drill capable of mining ore trapped deep under the surface.
Deep_Mining_Drill_Biofuel.flavorText: Slow progress, but its worth it

Deep_Mining_Drill_Electric.description: A convenient drilling device that runs on electricity.

Deer_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Deer.
Deer_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Deer_Statue_Stone.description: A graceful deer etched in stone.

Deer_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Dehumidifier.description: Powerful, portable protection against the effects of being underground.
Dehumidifier.flavorText: Powered by charcoal, the dehumidifier heavily reduces bacterial growth in caves by reducing dampness.

Delivery_Object.description: A fragile flechette flask containing temperature-sensitive terraforming enzyme payload.
Delivery_Object.flavorText: Following the ban on terraforming, Inaris continued to secretly pursue the technology under the protection of their owner-directors, Uniao.

Delivery_Object_Temperature.flavorText: Following the ban on terraforming, Inaris continued to secretly pursue the technology under the protection of their owner-directors, Uniao.

DesertWolf_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Hyena.
DesertWolf_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

DesertWolf_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Desert_Deer_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Antelope.
Desert_Deer_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Desert_Deer_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Desert_Mammoth_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Columbian Mammoth.
Desert_Mammoth_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Desert_Mammoth_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Desert_Striker_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Arid Striker.
Desert_Striker_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Desert_Striker_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Digested_Enzymes.description: Partially Digested Enzymes taken from the Stomach of Icarus Wildlife.

Dirt_Mound.description: A place to plant crops.  Fully-grown crops left too long will eventually wither and only provide spoiled plants.

Dogtags_Lure.description: A flashy lure carefully crafted out of... dogtags?
Dogtags_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Dough_Bread.description: Makes bread, just add to a fire.

Dough_Flatbread.description: Makes flatbread, just add to a fire.

Drac_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Drac.
Drac_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Drac_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Dreadwing_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Dreadwing.
Dreadwing_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Dreadwing_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Dried_Avocado.description: A snack with a chewy texture and concentrated flavor
Dried_Avocado.flavorText: Another great snack from your Drying Rack.

Dried_Freshwater_Fillet.description: A savory snack made by drying and preserving tender fillets of freshwater fish.
Dried_Freshwater_Fillet.flavorText: Can be dried using a Drying Rack. Rather chewy.

Dried_Rhubarb.description: A healthy snack with a rather tart flavor.
Dried_Rhubarb.flavorText: Another great snack from your Drying Rack.

Dried_Saltwater_Fillet.description: A flavorful snack made by drying and preserving tender fillets of saltwater fish.
Dried_Saltwater_Fillet.flavorText: Can be dried using a Drying Rack. Rather chewy.

Dried_Tomato.description: A snack with an intense sweet and savory flavor
Dried_Tomato.flavorText: Another great snack from your Drying Rack.

Dropship_Grenade_T4.description: Once thrown if the landing area is determined to be valid, will call your dropship to your current location.
Dropship_Grenade_T4.flavorText: Made on planet with the materials at hand, lets hope it works.

Dropship_Grenade_Workshop.description: Once thrown if the landing area is determined to be valid, will call your dropship to your current location.
Dropship_Grenade_Workshop.flavorText: Another amazing innovation thanks to Sinotai

Drying_Rack.description: A rack for slowly drying various cuts of meat and curing leather.

Dynamic_Mission_Beacon.description: Displays a map marker when deployed.
Dynamic_Mission_Beacon.flavorText: Lightly mapped and largely unexplored, human markers on the surface of Icarus are few and far between. The beacon offers a BYO solution.

Electric_Armor_Bench.description: Powered workbench for advanced textiles production and maintenance.

Electric_Dehumidifier_V2.description: Diminishes such health risks as pneumonia, while also seeming to dispel cave worms.
Electric_Dehumidifier_V2.flavorText: Whether cave worms are offended by the sudden aridity it produces, or the high pitched whine, research is yet to confirm.

Electric_Furnace_Large.description: A laboratory grade arc furnace, smelts basic and advanced materials alike.

Electric_Stove.flavorText: Less explosive than using home made biofuel.

Electronics.description: A modular control unit, adaptable to most I/Os.

Elephant_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Elephant.
Elephant_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Elephant_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Envirosuit.description: An entry-level S5 life support system from Xigo, Earths largest employer.
Envirosuit.flavorText: In theory, a Xigo general issue Self-contained Surface Survival Suit System (S5) offers full body environmental containment and air processing. How many wore this before you is unclear. While no longer entirely air-tight, the suit should still provide sufficient protection to the average user.

Envirosuit_Deluxe.description: A rare, early-model First Cohort envirosuit, issued exclusively to pioneer prospectors on the planet.
Envirosuit_Deluxe.flavorText: Originally issued by the UDA, these suits have subsequently become valuable collectors items. No longer available for purchase.

Envirosuit_Inaris_Alpha.description: An envirosuit with plenty of slots for upgrades to keep on your person.
Envirosuit_Inaris_Alpha.flavorText: Now theres a few less things to carry around with you.

Envirosuit_Larkwell_Alpha.description: A highly upgradable Envirosuit with expanded storage. Purpose built for the prospector who wants to carry it all.
Envirosuit_Larkwell_Alpha.flavorText: This suit was designed based on information gathered in a Larkwell Survey. When citing the issues they faced, prospectors ranked not enough pockets as their fourth greatest challenge.

Envirosuit_Larkwell_Bravo.description: The Larkwell Bulwark is your defense against the elements. Integrated with adaptive climate control technology.
Envirosuit_Larkwell_Bravo.flavorText: Designed for savage environmental conditions. Many prospectors will not set foot in the fringe zone without their Bulwark equipped... Better to die comfortable.

Envirosuit_Shengong.description: Enhanced heat resistance with extended resource and module capacity.
Envirosuit_Shengong.flavorText: Shengongs protextile system relies on ultra-high molecular weight thermoplastic cloth, offering lightweight heat protection and rapid 3D printability.

Envirosuit_Shengong_2.description: Offers reinforced insulation for cold-weather environments with extended resource and module capacity.
Envirosuit_Shengong_2.flavorText: Shengongs protextile system relies on ultra-high molecular weight thermoplastic cloth, offering lightweight protection and rapid 3D printability.

Envirosuit_Tier2.description: A general issue S5 envirosuit with extended life support systems.
Envirosuit_Tier2.flavorText: The Xigo S5-II is a full-spectrum environmental protection jumpsuit, helmet and life-support system, offering an augment slot and extended oxygen capacity.

Envirosuit_Tier3.description: An enhanced and lightly armored S5 envirosuit offering more functionality and life support systems than the S5-II.
Envirosuit_Tier3.flavorText: The Xigo S5-X is a surprisingly high-spec unit for the price. A complete survival system, it features basic rebreather technology and ultra-high-density polyethylene construction, reducing weight and increasing strength.

Envirosuit_Tier4.description: An upgraded S5-II suit with expanded resource storage.
Envirosuit_Tier4.flavorText: On Earth they judge you by your shoes, on Icarus by your Envirosuit.

Envirosuit_Tier5.description: A lightweight HDPE S5 Envirosuit providing expanded upgrade slots, light armor and respectable storage.
Envirosuit_Tier5.flavorText: Plastics come a long way since Tupperware

Envirosuit_Tier6.description: A lightly armored, double-module S5 suit with micro-texturing to reduce reflectivity.
Envirosuit_Tier6.flavorText: A 2124 survey registered the Xigo X as one of the most widely-recognized symbols in the world.

Envirosuit_Tier7.description: A broad spectrum, armored S5 envirosuit with dual module slots and decent resource capacity.
Envirosuit_Tier7.flavorText: Originally a website for price comparisons, the Xigo conglomerate grew to embrace distribution and, not long after, production. This was a seemingly indiscriminate expansion, focused not on one industry, but all of them - taking in so many fields that business analysts have largely rejected the idea of Xigo as a single entity.

Epoxy.description: A basic but strong and hard-setting organic polymer.
Epoxy.flavorText: UDA safety guidelines recommend not breathing in the fumes.

Equix_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Equix.
Equix_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Equix_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Exotic_Delivery_Interface.description: Allows you to order a Delivery Pod for Exotic Retrieval
Exotic_Delivery_Interface.flavorText: Part of the Icarus Orbital Exchange System developed by Sinotai.

Exotic_Harvester.description: A machine that harvests volatile raw exotics from trees in volcanic regions.
Exotic_Harvester.flavorText: A new machine for new types of Exotics!

Exotic_Processor.description: A machine that can process Volatile Exotics into usable materials.
Exotic_Processor.flavorText: You probably should still keep a good distance from this thing.

Exotic_Red.description: Exotic matter, an impossibility in your hands. Use an Orbital Exchange Interface to send to orbit.
Exotic_Red.flavorText: Like the other one, but Red.

Exotic_Red_Raw.description: Requires heavy processing to be of any use.

Explorers_Backpack.description: A handy backpack to help you on your travels.

Extractor_Biofuel.description: A portable, powered mining unit powered by biofuel for extracting exotics deposits.

Extractor_Electric.description: A portable, powered mining unit powered by electricity for extracting exotics deposits.
Extractor_Electric.flavorText: For all your exotic mining needs.

Extractor_Meta.description: Requires the IC-001 Power Source to Run

Fabricator.flavorText: Surprisingly simple for such a versatile machine, the Fabricator combines a flatbed CNC router with limited 3D alloy printing capabilities.

FactionMission_Tech1.description: Element from an experimental Larkwell Martinez device.
FactionMission_Tech1.flavorText: Some sort of signal or force transmitter.

FactionMission_Tech2.description: Element from an experimental Larkwell Martinez device.

FactionMission_Tech3.description: Element from an experimental Larkwell Martinez device.

FactionMission_TechRecombined.flavorText: While the precise operation of this Larkwell Martinez prototype is confidential, general specifications suggest it uses the mass-distorting effects of exotic matter to generate a diametric field intended to dampen local gravitic influence.

Faction_Mission_AquaScanner.description: A multi-purpose water monitoring, sampling and analysis station.
Faction_Mission_AquaScanner.flavorText: Hydrology is an often overlooked, but critical discipline, foundational to an astonishing array of scientific endeavor.

Faction_Mission_Drill.description: A portable, heavy duty boring rig powered by biofuel.
Faction_Mission_Drill.flavorText: Driven by bio-diesel, this micro-derrick design was adapted from asteroid mining equipment used in the early 22nd century.

Faction_Mission_Laser.description: A high intensity strontium vapor laser prototype.
Faction_Mission_Laser.flavorText: Exactly why Group 15 had experimental weapons grade laser equipment lying around is anyones guess.

Faction_Mission_Radar.flavorText: This inverse synthetic aperture radar was manufactured by Larkwell Martinez, a leading defense contractor with deep ties to the ACS.

Faction_Mission_WallDrill.description: An industrial-grade, portable electric mining rig designed for horizontal aperture drilling.
Faction_Mission_WallDrill.flavorText: This micro-derrick rig was adapted from Inaris-designed asteroid mining equipment used in the early 22nd century.

Farmers_Backpack.description: A handy backpack to cover all your farming needs.

Farmers_Shotgun.description: A crude shotgun hastily pulled together
Farmers_Shotgun.flavorText: A basic addition to your arsenal

Farming_CropPlot_T2_v2.description: A general-purpose planter bed for your crops. Fully-grown crops left too long will eventually wither and only provide spoiled plants.
Farming_CropPlot_T2_v2.flavorText: A raised planting bed brings the food to you, slowly.

Farming_CropPlot_T3_v2.description: A sturdy option for farming with water intake for faster crop growth. Fully-grown crops left too long will eventually wither and only provide spoiled plants.
Farming_CropPlot_T3_v2.flavorText: Can be connected to a water network

Farming_CropPlot_T4_v2.description: An advanced option for the busy farmer. Supports inputs from both Power and Water networks for increased crop growth speed. Fully-grown crops left too long will eventually wither and only provide spoiled plants.
Farming_CropPlot_T4_v2.flavorText: Can be connected to both a water and a power network

Farming_CropPlot_Workshop.description: Currently the best option for a farmer on Icarus. It uses a mix of nutrient dense mist and rich soil to promote growth and yield.
Farming_CropPlot_Workshop.flavorText: Can be connected to both a water and a power network

Fatty_Tbone.description: The largest of steaks can typically only be found in the largest of creatures

Fatty_Tbone_Cooked.description: A fiercely won, delicious steak dinner

Fatty_Tbone_Dried.description: A large, fatty piece of dried meat

Feather_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted from feathers, to attract more fish.
Feather_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Feet_Arms_Attachment_Fall_Resistance_1.description: An attachment that reduces falling damage taken and chance to receive a sprain.
Feet_Arms_Attachment_Fall_Resistance_1.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet or hands armor at an Alteration Bench.

Feet_Arms_Attachment_Fall_Resistance_2.description: An attachment that greatly reduces falling damage taken and chance to receive a sprain.
Feet_Arms_Attachment_Fall_Resistance_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet or hands armor at an Alteration Bench.

Feet_Body_Legs_Attachment_Stealth_Moveme.description: An attachment that reduces the threat while stealth and improves crouched movement speed.
Feet_Body_Legs_Attachment_Stealth_Moveme.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet, body or legs armor at an Alteration Bench.

Feet_Body_Legs_Attachment_Stealth_Moveme.description: An attachment that greatly reduces the threat while stealth and greatly improves crouched movement speed.
Feet_Body_Legs_Attachment_Stealth_Moveme.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet, body or legs armor at an Alteration Bench.

Feet_Legs_Attachment_Movement_Bonus_1.description: An attachment that improves swimming and climbing speed, and reduces jumping stamina cost.
Feet_Legs_Attachment_Movement_Bonus_1.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet or legs armor at an Alteration Bench.

Feet_Legs_Attachment_Movement_Bonus_2.description: An attachment that greatly improves swimming and climbing speed, and greatly reduces jumping stamina cost.
Feet_Legs_Attachment_Movement_Bonus_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to feet or legs armor at an Alteration Bench.

Fiber.description: A bundle of soft fiber, highly useful.
Fiber.flavorText: Fiber is collected from bast, the strong inner bark of certain flowering plants.

Fiber_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted out of fibre, to attract more fish.
Fiber_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Filletting_Station.description: A place to craft Rods and Lures and to fillet Fish that youve caught.

FireExtinguisher.description: A canister of compressed flame-extinguishing gel.
FireExtinguisher.flavorText: The instructions say: Aim towards flame.

FirePit.description: A large, stone-lined pit for swift cooking and heating.
FirePit.flavorText: Flashroast a steak or an entire mammoth forequarter.

FireWhacker.flavorText: Discovered in prehistory, the fire whacker represents an effective, if unsophisticated tactic: Attack the flames until they surrender.

Fire_Arrow.flavorText: One of the good things about being this far from Earth, theres no-one to tell you not to play with fire. - Sol Berlinski

Fireplace.description: Cooks food swiftly and safely. Basically a large enclosed firepit, for a more homely feel.
Fireplace.flavorText: On Icarus, fire is both friend and foe.

Fireplace_Chimney_Cap.description: The final step in a fireplace.

Fireplace_Chimney_Cap_Half.description: The final half-sized step in a fireplace.

Fireplace_Chimney_Ext.flavorText: Sometimes it felt like I had joined a rustic interior decoration cult - M. Le Baroni

Fish_Chunk_Stew.description: A hearty and flavorful soup made with tender chunks of fish and vegetables in a rich and savory broth.
Fish_Chunk_Stew.flavorText: Chop em up, cook em up, eat em up.

Fish_Chunks.description: A pile of roughly diced fish.

Fish_Fillet_Pie.description: A comforting and hearty dish made with a creamy filling of mixed fish and vegetables.
Fish_Fillet_Pie.flavorText: Stuffed to the brim with fish.

Fish_Wall_Mount.description: You may display your favourite catch here for all to see.

Fishing_Bench.description: A place to craft Rods and Lures and to fillet Fish that youve caught.

Flare_Arrow.description: Projects your position into the sky.
Flare_Arrow.flavorText: The lost among us lean heavily on this launchable marker.

Flashlight.description: An LED flashlight for illuminating dark corners.

Flint_Arrow.description: Flies further, hits harder than stone or bone.
Flint_Arrow.flavorText: Knappable flint provides a sharper arrowhead and greater penetration than stone or bone.

Food_Animal_Feed.flavorText: Seed feed to satiate your creatures needs.

Food_Berry_Bar.description: Full of energy for long hikes.
Food_Berry_Bar.flavorText: Tastes much better than seed crackers.

Food_Bread.description: Wholesome, filling and slow to spoil.

Food_Corn_Soup.description: A classic dish, even without shredded chicken.
Food_Corn_Soup.flavorText: Boosts stamina and improves endurance. Drains nostalgia.

Food_Creamed_Corn.description: Pureed corn, animal fat and water, easy to digest.
Food_Creamed_Corn.flavorText: Slow release energy with a baby-food consistency, boosting health and stamina.

Food_Crumbed_Fish_Fillet.description: Battered in breadcrumbs, lightly fried, boosts health and stamina.

Food_Fish_Dish.description: A simple curry with a large health boost.
Food_Fish_Dish.flavorText: Not the best fish curry in the galaxy, but far from the worst.

Food_Flatbread.flavorText: Simple to bake and easy to store, boosts health and stamina regen.

Food_Fried_Soy_Beans.description: Boosts health, lifts stamina, enhances self-satisfaction.
Food_Fried_Soy_Beans.flavorText: One of the original crops intended to sustain humanity on its first new extra-solar world.

Food_Fruit_Pie.description: Watermelon plus berries and pastry creates a passable, stamina boosting pie.

Food_Fruit_Salad.description: An all-natural, surprisingly delicious melon-berry mix, boosts stamina and health.
Food_Fruit_Salad.flavorText: A divisive dessert, loved or hated, and very little in between.

Food_Hearty_Salad.description: Gives a boost to health and stamina.

Food_Meat_Pie.description: A rustic pie that delivers a big health boost.
Food_Meat_Pie.flavorText: Stress cannot exist in the presence of a pie. - David Mamet

Food_Meat_Stew.flavorText: Some foods profit from rustic conditions. Boosts health, lifts stamina.

Food_Mushroom_Soup.description: A passable impression of a classic dish.
Food_Mushroom_Soup.flavorText: While some critics regard this meal as pointless if made without butter, purists do not last long on Icarus.

Food_Pickled_Carrot.flavorText: Like many other ancient ways, pickling has found a place on Icarus.

Food_Pickled_Tomato.description: Increases stamina, health regeneration, and shared XP.

Food_Potato_Bread.description: Improves stamina and keeps you fuller for longer.

Food_Potato_Carrot_Fries.description: Delivers a wide range of health benefits.

Food_Pumpkin_Bread.description: A noticeably yellow loaf that significantly increases endurance.
Food_Pumpkin_Bread.flavorText: Just like someone used to make.

Food_Roasted_Vegetables.description: A melange of cooked vegetables, provides a serious stamina boost.

Food_Seed_Bread.flavorText: Better for you than white bread... doesnt taste quite as good.

Food_Seed_Cracker.flavorText: This cracker resembles hardtack. Upholding the explorers tradition of terrible snack choices.

Food_Shepherds_Pie.description: An all rounder, this will keep you going.

Food_Trough.description: A basic trough to provide food for juvenile and tamed creatures. Accepts most fresh fruits and vegetables.

Food_Vegetable_Pie.description: Warm, health-giving, stamina-boosting - virtue in every pie.
Food_Vegetable_Pie.flavorText: If this pie had a slogan, it might be Stay delicious.

Food_Wild_Salad.description: Mixed pieces of squash and pumpkin at room temperature.
Food_Wild_Salad.flavorText: At home among the stars, yet no closer to answering the age old question: What is a salad, exactly?

Fortification_Wood_Gate.description: A large, strong wood gate fortification which can be opened and closed.
Fortification_Wood_Gate.flavorText: From safety to wilderness, an entryway to the danger of Icarus.

Fortification_Wood_Spikes.description: A large collection of spiked defenses which can be mounted to fortification walls.
Fortification_Wood_Spikes.flavorText: An extra layer of defense, prevents wildlife from working their way through your walls.

Fortification_Wood_Walkway.description: A walkway and ramp set for the wood fortification walls.
Fortification_Wood_Walkway.flavorText: A protected vantage point to survey the nearby area.

Fortification_Wood_Wall.description: A large, strong wood wall fortification.
Fortification_Wood_Wall.flavorText: Claim your territory through the wonders of construction.

Frag_Grenade.flavorText: Homemade explosives are the best kind.

Freshwater_Fillet_Curry.description: A spicy and aromatic dish made with tender pieces of fish cooked in a rich and creamy sauce with a blend of herbs and spices.
Freshwater_Fillet_Curry.flavorText: Spend the time on the sauce and reap the rewards.

Freshwater_Fish_Fillet.description: A neatly trimmed fillet ready for cooking.

Fried_Chunky_Vegetables.description: These veges are deep-fried until crispy and golden.
Fried_Chunky_Vegetables.flavorText: Another great meal from your Potbelly Stove.

Fried_Fish_Chunks.description: An easy snack for the hungry prospector whos short on time.
Fried_Fish_Chunks.flavorText: Not as fancy as a fillet, but just as filling.

Frozen_Ore.description: A chunk of frozen ore, must be heated to identify and use.
Frozen_Ore.flavorText: Avoid direct contact with eyes and/or skin.

Fruit_Muffin.flavorText: A delicious meal made on your Biofuel Stove.

Fur.description: One of natures more perfect insulation materials.
Fur.flavorText: Fur remains an exceptional material, especially in the terrazone, where temperatures are significantly cooler.

Fur_Arms.description: Heavy fur gloves, extremely warm with moderate physical protection.

Fur_Chest.description: An armored fur jacket, giving warmth and reasonable damage protection.

Fur_Feet.description: Heavily insulated fur boots, offering moderate physical protection.

Fur_Head.description: Heavy, warm and moderately protective headgear.

Fur_Legs.description: Heavy, strengthened fur leg armor, warm and moderately protective.

Gamey_Meat.description: Raw gamey meat, typically found amongst the more passive wildlife

Gamey_Meat_Cooked.description: A reasonably well cooked piece of meat

Gamey_Meat_Dried.description: A plain piece of dried meat

Geode_Lamp_Burst_Copper.flavorText: Bringing light, and style to your home on Icarus.

Ghillie_Arms.flavorText: Take the effort out of hunting.

Giant_Steak.flavorText: This should keep you going for a while

Giant_Steak_Cooked.description: A prime cut from the larger beasts

Giant_Steak_Dried.description: A large dried piece of meat

Glass.description: Despite its imperfections, a workable sheet of glass.
Glass.flavorText: Reflected in a sheet of glass is a simple fact: What looks familiar, is in fact a crystalline lattice unlike anything on Earth.

Glass_Beam.description: Anchors structures to the ground for higher building.
Glass_Beam.flavorText: Beams connect vertically and diagonally to support multi-level construction. Your HUD will indicate when beams are anchored with a blue cursor.

Glass_Half_Pitch.flavorText: A two part construction element, containing a base slope and an upper slope, for building low-pitched roofs.

Glass_Halfpiece.description: Half- and quarter-sized building elements for detailed construction work.
Glass_Halfpiece.flavorText: These sets are useful for creating walkways, balconies, trims and a range of other smaller constructions.

Glass_Jar.description: A roughly made, but perfectly serviceable mason jar.
Glass_Jar.flavorText: This jar is empty, but like the many gaps in our understanding of this planet, is waiting to be filled.

Glass_Jar_Jam.flavorText: Its not just jam. You hold in your hand an irreducible symbol of humanitys commitment to settling an alien world. Strongly increases max stamina.

Glass_Ramp.description: A transparent roof piece or ramp.
Glass_Ramp.flavorText: Able to be repaired with a repair hammer.

Glass_Roof_Corner.description: A transparent insert for angled roofs.

Glass_Wall.description: A fully transparent, mullioned wall section.
Glass_Wall.flavorText: Throw no stones, but hold R to cycle through variants, such as doorways. Mysteriously, can be repaired with a repair hammer.

Glass_Wall_Angle.description: Angular inserts for gables and other tilted designs.

Glassworking_Bench_V2.description: Tools for creating glass items and construction elements.
Glassworking_Bench_V2.flavorText: True glass-making originated in the Indus Valley in 1700 BCE, passing into the Mediterranean, then Africa and the rest of the world, before extending through space to Icarus in the mid 22nd century.

Iron_Door.description: A rough but resilient corrugated aluminium door.
Iron_Door.flavorText: Able to be repaired with a repair hammer.

Iron_Floor.description: Lightweight but resilient sheet aluminium flooring.
Iron_Floor.flavorText: Able to be repaired with a repair hammer.

Iron_Half_Pitch.flavorText: A two part construction element, containing a base slope and an upper slope, for building low-pitched roofs.

Iron_Halfpiece.description: Half- and quarter-sized building elements for detailed construction work.
Iron_Halfpiece.flavorText: These sets are useful for creating walkways, balconies, trims and a range of other smaller constructions.

Iron_Hammer.description: Maintain structures against the wrath of Icarus.
Iron_Hammer.flavorText: Counter the forces of nature with a little violence of your own.

Iron_Lure.description: A heavier lure carefully crafted out of iron, to attract more fish.
Iron_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Iron_Nail.flavorText: A nail works in two directions: through friction in the axial direction, and shear strength laterally.

Iron_Ramp.description: A lightweight sheet aluminium ramp or roofing sheet.
Iron_Ramp.flavorText: Able to be repaired with a repair hammer.

Kit_Concrete_Furnace.description: An insulated, high-temperature furnace for smelting a wide range of materials including steel.
Kit_Concrete_Furnace.flavorText: Icaruss oxygen levels may slow combustion, but ceramic insulation produces temperatures sufficient for smelting more advanced alloys.

Kit_Electric_Furnace.description: A laboratory grade arc furnace, smelts basic and advanced materials alike.

Kit_Extractor.description: A portable, powered mining unit for extracting exotics deposits.
Kit_Extractor.flavorText: Specifically designed to extract elanthium exotics. Operating tolerances not guaranteed for rarer exotic forms.

Kit_Floor_Torch.description: A free-standing torch requiring sticks for fuel.
Kit_Floor_Torch.flavorText: Oxygen levels may be a little lower, but fire provides light well enough.

Kit_Generator.description: An efficient, if basic biofuel-driven electric generator.
Kit_Generator.flavorText: Literally or figuratively, weve come a long way from the Faraday Disc.

Kit_Machining_Bench.description: Upgrades your manufacturing abilities with basic machine tools.

Kit_Mortar_And_Pestle.description: A simple tool for crafting resins, pastes, medicines and more.
Kit_Mortar_And_Pestle.flavorText: The tool of chefs, herbalists, apothecaries and alchemists.

Kit_Oxite_Dissolver.description: A more efficient oxidizer for processing oxite into oxygen.
Kit_Oxite_Dissolver.flavorText: Place oxite and an appropriate container into the dissolver to start filling it. Requires sulfur for fuel.

Kit_Radar.flavorText: This inverse synthetic aperture radar was manufactured by Larkwell Martinez, a leading defense contractor with deep ties to the ACS.

Kit_Skinning_Bench.description: Fully processes animal carcasses for more resources.
Kit_Skinning_Bench.flavorText: As any hunter knows, preparing an animal can be a slow, messy, wasteful task. The right tools make all the difference.

Kit_Stone_Furnace.description: A simple stone furnace for smelting iron and copper.
Kit_Stone_Furnace.flavorText: Bronze-age technology, spread to the stars.

Kit_Wall_Torch.description: A mounted flame for adorning shelter walls.
Kit_Wall_Torch.flavorText: Lower oxygen levels produce a dirty, but workable flame.

Kit_Wood_Cupboard.description: A place to put necessities ... and the rest.

Kitchen_Bench.description: A modular workspace for cooking and concocting complex recipes.

Kitchen_Storage.description: A compact module for all your kitchen storage needs.

Kitchen_Stove.flavorText: A well-crafted, solidly insulated stove for discerning off-world chefs.

LightningRod_Basic.flavorText: The effect of Minoss gravitational tides on the atmosphere creates extraordinarily powerful electrical storms, making these devices indispensible.

Lily.description: A wildflower reputed to have medicinal properties.
Lily.flavorText: Adapting to the exotics-infused soil of Icarus, this lily has acquired unusual and useful new chemical properties.

Longbow.description: A powerful, but heavy long-range weapon.
Longbow.flavorText: Xeno-biologists hurriedly altered the genes of the tree from which this weapon is made, so that it might thrive on Icarus, never imagining that one day, a bow would be fashioned from it.

Machete.description: A heavy duty blade, highly durable but less suitable for skinning.

Mammoth_Tusk.description: A fortune in ivory from a titan reborn; a small step towards revealing Icaruss secrets.
Mammoth_Tusk.flavorText: Theories suggest that when exotic material present in plant life is ingested, it affects cellular reproduction in animals. The exact mechanism is unclear, with speculation that some varieties of exotics possess negative mass, producing relativistic micro-effects. Analysis of this specimen will reveal more.

Masonry_Bench.description: Tools for working and shaping stone.
Masonry_Bench.flavorText: The art of stonework is untouched by the distance between worlds.

Masonry_Bench_T3.description: A manual workspace for crafting simple building supplies, weapons, and tools.
Masonry_Bench_T3.flavorText: The skill and precision of a mason can never be replaced by machines...

Masonry_Bench_T4.description: Powered bench for heavy stonework and carving.

Material_Processor.description: Swiftly craft advanced ingredients and resources.

Medic_Backpack.description: A handy backpack to cover all your medical needs.

MetaResource.description: Exotic matter, an impossibility in your hands. Use an Orbital Exchange Interface to send to orbit.
MetaResource.flavorText: Previously believed to exist only in the heart of stars, the most common form of exotics, elanthium, has permitted extraordinary leaps in low temperature super conductors and high-density power storage.

Meta_Antibiotic_Vaccine_Alpha.flavorText: Strong but short-acting, these phage-based vaccines generally last for several days - long enough to cover most expeditions to the surface.

Meta_Arrow_Printed_Alpha.flavorText: With the advent of widespread, domestic metallic 3D printing, modern archery entered a golden age of specialist bickering about arow design and composition.

Meta_Arrow_Printed_Beta.flavorText: The non-lethal, but highly effective toxin skirts a number of international - and interplanetary - chemical weapons agreements.

Meta_Arrow_Printed_Charlie.description: Metallic 3D printed arrows with a micro-barbed head designed for inflicting lethal wounds.
Meta_Arrow_Printed_Charlie.flavorText: The legality of these projectiles is currently unclear.

Meta_Arrow_Set_Shengong.description: 25 arrows of decent quality, if unremarkable performance. CONSUME to open bundle.
Meta_Arrow_Set_Shengong.flavorText: Shengong Inc. are a wholly owned subsidary of Sinotai.

Meta_Arrow_Shengong.description: Arrows of decent quality, if unremarkable performance.
Meta_Arrow_Shengong.flavorText: Shengong is the sister company of C.H.A.C., specializing in off-world equipment and weaponry.

Meta_Avocado_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Avocado Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Axe.description: A mass-produced, but unremarkable hewing tool.
Meta_Axe.flavorText: Xigo specialises in high-end look at a low-end price.

Meta_Axe_Inaris_Alpha.description: An axe geared towards felling trees and chopping lumber
Meta_Axe_Inaris_Alpha.flavorText: Discovering how to mine meteors really changed the game for Inaris

Meta_Axe_Inaris_Charlie.description: A solid addition to your belt

Meta_Axe_Inaris_Delta.flavorText: Uniao owns the site of Earths first space elevator

Meta_Axe_Larkwell.description: A well-honed, but less durable axe.
Meta_Axe_Larkwell.flavorText: Larkwell Martinez is an old US-based industrial conglomerate with strong presence in off-world infrastructure.

Meta_Axe_Printed.flavorText: The MX Collective provides 90% of printing designs to the ever-expanding AM market.

Meta_Axe_Shengong_Alpha.description: A single-bit axe with 3D-printed handle and metallic head.
Meta_Axe_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: While the Heike delivers a lot more wood with every strike, this lightweight power comes at the cost of swifter wear and tear.

Meta_Axe_Shengong_Beta.description: An efficient, if less than durable harvesting implement.
Meta_Axe_Shengong_Beta.flavorText: Shengong Inc. was founded by Sinotai in 2082 CE.

Meta_Axe_Shengong_Charlie.description: A basic, but respectable felling tool.
Meta_Axe_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: For a single, simple reason, handtools such as this experienced a resurgence as humanity settle worlds other than Earth: reliability.

Meta_Axe_Shengong_Delta.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Axe. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Axe_Shengong_Delta.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Axe_Shengong_Echo.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Axe. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Axe_Shengong_Echo.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Backpack_Larkwell_Alpha.description: Provides excellent utilities for those who prefer a shotgun to a bow.
Meta_Backpack_Larkwell_Alpha.flavorText: Larkwell Martinez have been well known earthside since before Icarus was even discovered.

Meta_Backpack_Larkwell_Beta.description: Provides a huge boost to your storage capacity.

Meta_Bow_Larkwell.flavorText: For moments when remaining stealth is paramount.

Meta_Bow_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: Shengong designs are not designed to last, but rather, for ease of repair, being defined by the high degree of interchangeability of parts between their products.

Meta_Bow_Shengong_Beta.description: A powerful, if not especially durable recurve design.

Meta_Bow_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: A Shengong knock-off of a classic design.

Meta_Canteen_Inaris.description: A canteen that adds Electrolytes to your water for quicker stamina recovery.
Meta_Canteen_Inaris.flavorText: A must-have for the savvy adventurer.

Meta_Canteen_Larkwell.description: A trusty drinking vessel using modern tech.
Meta_Canteen_Larkwell.flavorText: The ACS use these exclusively on their own missions.

Meta_Canteen_Shengong.description: A durable and economic water container.
Meta_Canteen_Shengong.flavorText: Exactly how the Hulu became such an icon of off-world existence is lost in a froth of interplanetary memes.

Meta_Carbon_Arms_Alpha.description: A lightweight piece of armor designed with stealth and movement in mind.
Meta_Carbon_Arms_Alpha.flavorText: Please report any unusal side effects to your local UDA office.

Meta_Carbon_Arms_Beta.description: The latest technology designed to assist with mining and felling.
Meta_Carbon_Arms_Beta.flavorText: Youll find you can lift more with this set.
