Meta_Coal_Set.flavorText: Retrieved, processed, compressed from stellar leftovers.

Meta_Creature_Scanner.description: Bio-Entity Analysis and Scanning Technology. A handheld device that scans nearby creatures for analysis and locates weaknesses.
Meta_Creature_Scanner.flavorText: A beauty of a device that will make surviving Icarus that much easier.

Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_A.description: A high powered Crossbow thats quick to reload.

Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_B.description: The heavy draw on this weapon causes a slower reload, but adds far more damage.
Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_B.flavorText: Be careful where you point that thing.

Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_C.description: A reliable crossbow to give you an edge in combat.
Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_C.flavorText: Hated by bears all over Icarus.

Meta_Crossbow_Inaris_D.flavorText: This should give you an edge against the wildlife.

Meta_Fiber_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Fiber Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Fishfinder.description: Fish Identification and Scanning Hardware. A handheld device that scans the waterbodies at the present location for fish like creatures.

Meta_Frag_Larkwell.flavorText: Larkwell Martinez is a prominent defence contractor to the ACS and its allies.

Meta_Furnace_Printed.description: A premade furnace for all of your basic smelting needs
Meta_Furnace_Printed.flavorText: Basic but gets the job done

Meta_GreenTea_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Tea Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Hammer_Larkwell.description: A well made, mid-range repair hammer.

Meta_Hammer_Printed.flavorText: Counter the forces of nature with a little violence of your own.

Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Alpha.description: A highly economic and affordable repair hammer, like so many Shengong products.
Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: Shengong resolve the scarcity of replacement parts in space by ensuring its products share many common parts.

Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Beta.description: A highly economic and affordable design, like so many Shengong products.
Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Beta.flavorText: From hammers to space stations, Shengong Inc makes it all.

Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Charlie.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Hammer. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Hammer_Shengong_Echo.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Heated_Canteen_Larkwell.description: An advanced canteen that can be used to heat and store water at your desired temperature.
Meta_Heated_Canteen_Larkwell.flavorText: Because theres nothing better than a hot drink in the Arctic.

Meta_Knife.description: A low grade, serviceable knife from the Purveyor of Everything
Meta_Knife.flavorText: Whatever you kill with this blade doesnt need to know how little you paid.

Meta_Knife_Inaris_Alpha.description: The perfect knife for hunting and skinning
Meta_Knife_Inaris_Alpha.flavorText: Inaris is partly owned by the Uniao alliance

Meta_Knife_Inaris_Bravo.flavorText: Brutal, but it gets the job done

Meta_Knife_Inaris_Charlie.description: A trusty blade to keep by your side
Meta_Knife_Inaris_Charlie.flavorText: Perfect for hurling at your enemies

Meta_Knife_Inaris_Delta.description: The perfect knife to hone your skills with

Meta_Knife_Larkwell.description: A keen blade, honed to perfection.
Meta_Knife_Larkwell.flavorText: Larkwell Martinez is well-known as a manufacturer of hard-hitting weapons.

Meta_Knife_Printed.description: A 3D printed metal hunting knife of no great quality.
Meta_Knife_Printed.flavorText: A staple of metallic AM printing, which has probably made its designer a small fortune in licensing fees.

Meta_Knife_Shengong_Alpha.description: A heavy, powerful blade, but takes extra energy to use effectively.
Meta_Knife_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: An iconic knife found wherever humanity has spread, the Qies weight makes it a potent, if sometimes punishing weapon.

Meta_Knife_Shengong_Beta.flavorText: The knife of the family does not cut. ~ Proverb

Meta_Knife_Shengong_Charlie.description: A strong, if weighty close quarters weapon.
Meta_Knife_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: A knife does not recognise its owner. ~ Proverb

Meta_Knife_Shengong_Delta.description: A basic but brutal straight-back skinning knife.
Meta_Knife_Shengong_Delta.flavorText: A rough weapon for tough conditions - slice, skin, stab or throw the Sichou, and watch your fingers.

Meta_Knife_Shengong_Echo.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Knife. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Knife_Shengong_Echo.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Lily_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Lily Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Module_Alpha.description: Enables prospectors near you to carry more weight. Buff does not apply to the wearer.

Meta_Module_Animal_Healthbar.description: A fast way to view the health of your prey, or your enemies
Meta_Module_Animal_Healthbar.flavorText: Remember to keep an eye on your own health bar too

Meta_Module_Animal_Highlighting.description: A quicker way to track your prey

Meta_Module_Beta.description: Enables prospectors near you to heal from afflictions faster. Buff does not apply to the wearer.

Meta_Module_Carry_Weight.description: Electro-active device that hijacks metallic envirosuit fibers to create a virtual exoskeleton that enhances carry capacity.
Meta_Module_Carry_Weight.flavorText: Electro-active shape-memory fibers are highly flexible under normal conditions, but become rigid when exposed to an electric charge.

Meta_Module_Caving.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit in protecting you from threats found in the cave systems of Icarus.
Meta_Module_Caving.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Module_Consumption.description: Micro-doses the user with a high-potency enzyme supplement to reduce food, water and oxygen consumption.
Meta_Module_Consumption.flavorText: Like terraforming for your body. - Anonymous Group 15 researcher

Meta_Module_Extremes.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit in regulating your temperature in extreme environments.
Meta_Module_Extremes.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Module_Fall_Damage.description: Drastic movement causes a piezoelectric sensor to deliver an electric charge to a small fragment of exotics, briefly reducing mass and diminishing fall damage.

Meta_Module_Fire_Resistance.description: Improves fire resistance by harnessing exotics quasi-negative mass to create a nonlinear energy sink.
Meta_Module_Fire_Resistance.flavorText: The sudden abundance of exotic matter produced an immense range of technological innovation in an exceedingly short time, resulting in an era for which the world renaissance is barely adequate.

Meta_Module_Fishing.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit in locating a greater variety of aquatic life in the waterways of Icarus.
Meta_Module_Fishing.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Module_Movement.flavorText: Experiments by Larkwell Martinez into the gravitational effects of exotics have resulted in a prototype known as the Dampener, which slightly lowers local mass, allowing swifter movement.

Meta_Module_PlayerTracker.description: Provides realtime location data on team members.
Meta_Module_PlayerTracker.flavorText: Equip in a module slot to view your team members on the map.

Meta_Module_Poison_Resistance.description: Releases a steady micro dose of antivenom, enhancing poison resistance.
Meta_Module_Poison_Resistance.flavorText: The Detoxifier is classified under UDA regulations as technically qualifying users as a cyborg.

Meta_Module_Taming.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit with pheromones to encourage the best from your tamed creatures.
Meta_Module_Taming.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Module_Temperature.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit in regulating minor temperature fluctuations.
Meta_Module_Temperature.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Module_WorldBoss.description: Provides realtime location data on World Bosses
Meta_Module_WorldBoss.flavorText: Equip in a module slot to view your world bosses on the map.

Meta_Module_Wounds.description: A handy module that assists your envirosuit with extra layers of protection against flesh wounds.
Meta_Module_Wounds.flavorText: Warning: Prototype tech listed off-label for use in Icarus operations. Warranty void if used planetside. Use at your own risk.

Meta_Mushroom_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Mushroom Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Oxygen_Gel.description: Agrizeros patented gel supplement lowers the heart rate, reducing oxygen consumption.
Meta_Oxygen_Gel.flavorText: Largely illegal on Earth, indispensible among the stars.

Meta_Oxygen_Tank_Larkwell.description: An advanced oxygen tank with brand-new filters to improve vigor and air quality planetside.
Meta_Oxygen_Tank_Larkwell.flavorText: A true breath of fresh air.

Meta_Oxygen_Tank_Shengong.flavorText: Named in memory of Yang Liwei.

Meta_Pickaxe.description: A fancy name for a fairly ordinary mining device.
Meta_Pickaxe.flavorText: Theres a joke: Where Xigo goes, humanity is never far behind.

Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Alpha.description: A heavy tool to mine with off-world

Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Bravo.description: A metal base gives this mining axe great grip
Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Bravo.flavorText: Mining is where all began for Inaris

Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Charlie.description: A base model that performs well

Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Delta.description: A sturdy pickaxe that gets the job done
Meta_Pickaxe_Inaris_Delta.flavorText: Perfect for mining, or scaring away that pesky wildlife

Meta_Pickaxe_Larkwell.flavorText: One of Larkwell Martinezs flagship products.

Meta_Pickaxe_Printed.flavorText: The MX Collective provides a vast range of AM designs for a small licensing fee.

Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Alpha.description: A high yield, heavy mining tool from an industrial giant.
Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: Typically for Shengong, the Kuangs weight translates to power and improved results, but tends to slow and tire its users.

Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Beta.description: A robust and hard-bladed alloy steel mining axe.
Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Beta.flavorText: A tool to break the soil of many worlds.

Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Charlie.description: A serviceable pickaxe, with an edge for fine metal.
Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: Until it came to seem outdated, Shengong branded itself as Armorer to the Solar System.

Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Delta.description: A basic pickaxe, robust if mass-produced.
Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Delta.flavorText: A pick axe aint never run outta power. - Sol Berlinski

Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Echo.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Pickaxe. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Pickaxe_Shengong_Echo.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Potato_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Potato Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Power_Source.description: Used to power the IC-001 Extractor. Single use. Cannot be returned to Station.
Meta_Power_Source.flavorText: WARNING: Handle with care, contains unstable material.

Meta_Pumpkin_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Pumpkin Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Ration.flavorText: For those with more pressing concerns than what their food actually tastes like, Agrizeros MREs provide enduring sustenance.

Meta_Reed_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Reed Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Repair_Item.description: A kit that can repair most workshop items at a Repair Bench.
Meta_Repair_Item.flavorText: If you break it, buy this.

Meta_Repair_Item_Pack.description: Use to collect 5x Workshop Repair Kits that can repair most Workshop Items at a Repair Bench.

Meta_Scanner_DeepOre.description: A scanner that can be programmed to locate specific deep ore deposits within the surrounding area
Meta_Scanner_DeepOre.flavorText: The best that money can buy.

Meta_Sickle_Larkwell.description: A mid-range sickle, perfect for gathering.
Meta_Sickle_Larkwell.flavorText: If it aint broken, why fix it?

Meta_Sickle_Printed.description: A metallic polymer blade, increasing harvesting yield.
Meta_Sickle_Printed.flavorText: MXC is a highly successful collective focused on licensing 3D printing blueprints.

Meta_Spear_Inaris_Alpha.description: Slow your foes with this hunting spear

Meta_Spear_Inaris_Bravo.description: A sturdily built spear with excellent grip

Meta_Spear_Inaris_Charlie.description: A well made spear thats also lightweight
Meta_Spear_Inaris_Charlie.flavorText: Inaris are central players in the off-world mining industry

Meta_Spear_Inaris_Delta.description: A reliable addition to your arsenal
Meta_Spear_Inaris_Delta.flavorText: Keep your weapons by your side, youll never know when youll need them

Meta_Spear_Larkwell.description: A tough and deadly multi-purpose weapon.
Meta_Spear_Larkwell.flavorText: The LM brand has a very enthusiastic user base for its products.

Meta_Spear_Printed.description: A low quality, but perfectly serviceable 3D printed spear.
Meta_Spear_Printed.flavorText: Using techniques pioneered in the early 21st century, additive manufacturing has rendered metal the new plastic.

Meta_Spear_Shengong_Alpha.description: The Xingxing may not excel in any area, but represents unalloyed adequacy.
Meta_Spear_Shengong_Alpha.flavorText: No weapons are more widespread in human space than Shengongs.

Meta_Spear_Shengong_Beta.description: Doesnt need to last a lifetime, to save one.
Meta_Spear_Shengong_Beta.flavorText: Shengongs designs excel in no particular areas, but as a result have produced many classics of design economy.

Meta_Spear_Shengong_Charlie.description: A decent spear that knows exactly what it is.
Meta_Spear_Shengong_Charlie.flavorText: Shengong is a subsidary of Asias space administration, Sinotai. Its operation may be highly beauracratic, but its products are legendary for their efficiency.

Meta_Spear_Shengong_Delta.description: A minor miracle of low cost production.

Meta_Spear_Shengong_Echo.description: A brand new take on the classic Prospectors Spear. The next generation of tools on Icarus.
Meta_Spear_Shengong_Echo.flavorText: Brought to you by Shengong - the Brand of the People.

Meta_Squash_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Squash Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Stamina_Gel.description: A blend of natural ingredients and highly synthetic stimulants that temporarily slows stamina loss.

Meta_Strawberry_Seed.description: Right click to open a packet of Strawberry Seeds that have been stabilised for off-world farming

Meta_Super_Ration.description: Protein- and energy- boosted high-density food product.
Meta_Super_Ration.flavorText: Agrizeros Eat and forget campaign never truly hit home, suggesting the food was either immemorable or best wiped from ones memory. Regardless, the product provides a huge amount of nutrition in a small space.

Metal_Axe.description: An iron axe, for swifter felling and hewing.
Metal_Axe.flavorText: Technological progress is like an axe in the hands of a pathological criminal. -- Albert Einstein

Metal_Bed.description: A sleek and minimalist metal bed.
Metal_Bed.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Bolt.description: A hard-hitting iron bolt, trading distance for damage.
Metal_Bolt.flavorText: Roughly 64,000 years since its first invention, the essential form of the bolt remains unchanged.

Metal_Bookshelf.description: A sleek and minimalist metal bookshelf.
Metal_Bookshelf.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Display_Cabinet.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Dresser.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Knife.description: A short, clip-point blade for better defense and swifter skinning.
Metal_Knife.flavorText: A mind all logic is like a knife all blade. It makes the hand bleed that uses it. -- Rabindranath Tagore

Metal_Ladder.description: A sturdy metal ladder for climbing.

Metal_Lamp.description: A sleek and minimalist metal lamp.
Metal_Lamp.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Nightstand.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Ore.description: Natural iron ore of high purity, easily smelted.
Metal_Ore.flavorText: Iron ore is plentiful in the planetary crust, as on Earth. Requires the high temperatures of a furnace to refine into pure ingots.

Metal_Oxite_Dissolver.description: A faster and more efficient, biofuel-powered oxidizer with greater storage.

Metal_Pickaxe.description: A strong iron pickaxe, for more rapid, reliable mining of basic stone.
Metal_Pickaxe.flavorText: An enduring if ironic icon of the so-called Exotics Rush.

Metal_Shelf_Wall.description: A sleek and minimalist metal wall shelf.
Metal_Shelf_Wall.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Sledgehammer.description: Very heavy weapon that can be used to break rocks like Scoria and Obsidian.
Metal_Sledgehammer.flavorText: Can deal a lot of damage

Metal_Spear.description: An iron spearhead, improving defensive power and range.
Metal_Spear.flavorText: I throw a spear into the darkness. That is intuition. Then I must send an army into the darkness to find the spear. That is intellect. -- Ingmar Bergman

Metal_Stool.description: A sleek and minimalist metal stool.
Metal_Stool.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Table_Dining10.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Table_Dining6.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Table_Round.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Metal_Wardrobe.description: A sleek and minimalist metal wardrobe.
Metal_Wardrobe.flavorText: Designed for functionality and a touch of urban elegance.

Mining_Backpack.description: A reinforced backpack that greatly reduces the weight of ore and wood carried.
Mining_Backpack.flavorText: For long-distance hauling and concerted construction pushes, the triple-layer leatherwork and heavy framing greatly reduces burdens.

Mission_Analyzer_Egg.description: Scans and locates nearby organic matter of the same type.
Mission_Analyzer_Egg.flavorText: Another machine designed by a scientist who has never stepped foot on Icarus.

Mission_AudioLog_Prometheus_1.description: A Strange Audio log taken from a prospectors suit.

Mission_AudioLog_Prometheus_2.description: A Strange Audio log taken from a prospectors suit.

Mission_Broken_Prototype_Laser.description: Broken prototype laser, it could be repaired at a crafting bench.
Mission_Broken_Prototype_Laser.flavorText: Once a cutting edge prototype, now a pile of scrap.

Mission_Broken_Solar_Panel.description: Could be repaired with a bit of patience
Mission_Broken_Solar_Panel.flavorText: A lot of simple devices can be repaired on Icarus

Mission_CaveWormEgg.description: An egg snatched from a caveworm nest.

Mission_Communication_Blueprint_T2.description: A USB drive with the plans for an Upgraded Communication Device
Mission_Communication_Blueprint_T2.flavorText: Once downloaded to the suit, there is no need for this item.

Mission_Communication_Device_T2.description: Interact to Receive a Mission From SMPL3 - Simplified Mission Prospector Liaison V3
Mission_Communication_Device_T2.flavorText: Replacing UDA agents one mission at a time.

Mission_Communication_Device_T3.description: An upgrade for the C0NT4CT Device that will allow access to encoded missions.

Mission_Communication_Device_T4.description: An upgrade for the C0NT4CT Device that will allow access to encrypted missions.

Mission_Damaged_Bioweapon_Sample.description: A damaged bio-weapon, it seems to be leaking.
Mission_Damaged_Bioweapon_Sample.flavorText: Probably get rid of this ASAP

Mission_Delivery_Crystal.flavorText: This crystal seems to be a perfect candidate for large scale map resonance

Mission_Device.description: Certified Online Network Transmitter for Contractor Tasking. Grants access to SMPL3 Missions and Operations.
Mission_Device.flavorText: Replacing UDA agents one mission at a time.

Mission_Digested_Biomatter_Sample.description: A sample taken from a contaminated bear.
Mission_Digested_Biomatter_Sample.flavorText: Its essentially some kind of Acid

Mission_Empty_Enzyme_Container.description: A container which used to hold stable Enzymes
Mission_Empty_Enzyme_Container.flavorText: Not a trace of enzymes remain.

Mission_Explosive.description: An explosive device provided by the UDA for special operations.

Mission_Flora_Biomatter_Sample.description: A sample taken from a poisonous plant

Mission_Full_Enzyme_Container.description: A container full of partially digested Enzymes.

Mission_HighTech_1.description: A small, minutely detailed object, extremely light to hold.
Mission_HighTech_1.flavorText: Close attention reveals a faint humming, or perhaps you are imagining it.

Mission_HighTech_2.description: A clearly functional item, with no clear function.
Mission_HighTech_2.flavorText: Something about this device feels immensely old.

Mission_HighTech_3.description: An ornately manufactured device of uncertain materials.
Mission_HighTech_3.flavorText: Wherever this came from, and whoever made it, you are certain youve never seen anything like it before.

Mission_HighTech_Assembled.description: A device of uncertain age, properties and origin.
Mission_HighTech_Assembled.flavorText: Something about this device just feels wrong, though whether its the uncanny weight, the extraordinary intricacy, its arcane purpose, or something else, who can say?

Mission_Knife_Lion.description: Exotic infused blade, good for gathering rare meat
Mission_Knife_Lion.flavorText: Sharp with a faint purple glow.

Mission_Laser_Part_1.description: The base for a high-powered heating device
Mission_Laser_Part_1.flavorText: An excellent example of sturdy construction

Mission_Laser_Part_2.description: The arm for a high-powered heating device
Mission_Laser_Part_2.flavorText: Keep fingers and toes clear from all moving parts

Mission_Laser_Part_3.description: The laser for a high-powered heating device

Mission_Power_Source.description: A state of the art Power Cell for a Biological Containment Unit.
Mission_Power_Source.flavorText: This is making a very weird humming noise.

Mission_Prototype_Battery.flavorText: Strangely heavy for its size, the low hum it emits is slightly unnerving

Mission_Prototype_Laser.description: The result of a makeshift repair.

Mission_Prototype_Printed_Crate.description: A 3D Printed Crate with an internal battery for keeping contents preserved.

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Abyssal_Oxite.description: A unstable form of Oxite found deep underground
Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Abyssal_Oxite.flavorText: You feel a weird burning sensation..

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Bomb.description: A device used for monitoring the nearby environment.
Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Bomb.flavorText: A hospitable terraspace was the goal..

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_BombParts.description: A control system for an environmental monitoring device.
Mission_STYX_D_Research2_BombParts.flavorText: Some circuitry, a little tape, good as new.

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Catalyst.description: A catalyst to stabilize volatile materials.
Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Catalyst.flavorText: Making it a little safer to handle certain raw materials.

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Containment.flavorText: Preventing mortal injury to prospectors is good for the bottom line.

Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Scanner.description: A device designed to monitor the effects of Abyssal Oxite on organic life.
Mission_STYX_D_Research2_Scanner.flavorText: The things we do for Ren.

Mission_Ship_Cargo.description: The ACS seem to want this pretty badly.
Mission_Ship_Cargo.flavorText: What is this? How does it work? One of lifes great mysteries...

Mission_Ship_Gyro.flavorText: This is just what this ship needs to get back home.

Mission_Ship_Gyro_Broken.description: This instrument has been damaged almost beyond repair.
Mission_Ship_Gyro_Broken.flavorText: What could have broken this so badly?

Mission_Ship_Navigation.description: A Navigation Module for a Ship held together with materials found on planet.

Mission_Ship_Navigation_Part.description: A few electrical parts with frayed wires.
Mission_Ship_Navigation_Part.flavorText: Can be repaired on a Machining Bench

Mission_Ship_Thruster.description: A quickly repaired basic thruster made from on materials found on planet.
Mission_Ship_Thruster.flavorText: How did this work to begin with?

Mission_Ship_Thruster_Part.description: The remains of what was a Ship Thruster.
Mission_Ship_Thruster_Part.flavorText: Can be repaired on a Machining Bench

Mission_Ship_Thruster_Salvaged.description: A salvaged basic thruster found in some debris.
Mission_Ship_Thruster_Salvaged.flavorText: How did this work to begin with?

Mission_Sonic_Disrupter.description: An experimental device for projecting densely clustered micro-shockwaves in a gas medium.
Mission_Sonic_Disrupter.flavorText: A product of collaborative research between Group 15 and one of Larkwell Martinezs non-lethal weapons research units.

Mission_Tomato.description: A tomato spliced with the genes of a goat for surviving harsh climates.
Mission_Tomato.flavorText: Classed as a fruit, not a vegetable.

Mixed_Berries.description: A tasty combination of berries to keep you going.
Mixed_Berries.flavorText: Another great meal from your Cooking Station.

Moa_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Moa.
Moa_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Moa_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Module_Compass.description: An inertial compass system for an Envirosuit.
Module_Compass.flavorText: Equip in a module slot to activate your Envirosuits Compass Module.

Module_Creature_Tracker.description: Equipping this item to an Auxiliary slot will allow you to see all alive creatures

Module_Player_Status.flavorText: Equip in an module slot to monitor team status info.

Module_Player_Tracker.description: Provides realtime location data on team members.
Module_Player_Tracker.flavorText: Equip in a module slot to view your team members on the map.

Module_Waypoint.description: A GPS-based unit for setting and managing waypoints.
Module_Waypoint.flavorText: Equip in an module slot to enable waypoint marking.

Molotov.flavorText: Homemade explosives are the best kind.

Mushroom.description: A nutritious fungus, can be eaten raw, but best fried.
Mushroom.flavorText: The full implications of introducing fungi to a new world are yet to be seen.

Needler_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Needler.
Needler_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Needler_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Obsidian.description: Glass formed from the belly of the earth, as chunks of solid lava.
Obsidian.flavorText: Very popular for use in both weapons and jewellery.

Obsidian_Arms.description: A durable piece of armor that provides a fair level of resistance against fire and heat.
Obsidian_Arms.flavorText: Proof that anything can be salvaged for use on Icarus.

Obsidian_Arrow.description: A lightweight arrow created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Obsidian_Arrow.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Axe.description: A lightweight Axe created with a sharpened head of Obsidian. Gives a chance to collect coal from trees.
Obsidian_Axe.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Bolt.description: A lightweight bolt created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Obsidian_Bolt.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Chest.description: A durable piece of armor that provides a fair level of resistance against fire and heat.
Obsidian_Chest.flavorText: Proof that anything can be salvaged for use on Icarus.

Obsidian_Feet.flavorText: Proof that anything can be salvaged for use on Icarus.

Obsidian_Head.description: A durable piece of armor that provides a fair level of resistance against fire and heat.
Obsidian_Head.flavorText: Proof that anything can be salvaged for use on Icarus.

Obsidian_Knife.description: A lightweight knife created with a sharpened blade of Obsidian. Gives a chance for food to be instantly cooked when skinning.
Obsidian_Knife.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Legs.description: A durable piece of armor that provides a fair level of resistance against fire and heat.
Obsidian_Legs.flavorText: Proof that anything can be salvaged for use on Icarus.

Obsidian_Pickaxe.description: A lightweight Pickaxe created with a sharpened point of Obsidian. Gives a chance to instantly smelt ore when mining.
Obsidian_Pickaxe.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Sickle.description: A lightweight sickle created with a sharpened blade of Obsidian. Gives a chance to cook veges when harvesting but may also produce spoiled plants.
Obsidian_Sickle.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Sledgehammer.description: A lightweight hammer created with a blunted block of Obsidian. Gives a chance to instantly smelt ore when mining.
Obsidian_Sledgehammer.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Spear.description: A lightweight spear created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Obsidian_Spear.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Throwing_Knife.description: A lightweight throwing knife created with a sharpened blade of Obsidian.
Obsidian_Throwing_Knife.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Obsidian_Throwing_Spear.description: An aerodynamic spear created with a sharpened point of Obsidian.
Obsidian_Throwing_Spear.flavorText: Made using volcanic glass created from the bowels of the planet, that has cooled rapidly with minimal crystal growth.

Organic_Resin.description: A natural and highly flexible bonding agent.

Oxite.description: Can be refined into breathable oxygen.
Oxite.flavorText: A stable water-oxygen matrix, oxite slowly decomposes when exposed to the atmosphere of Icarus.

Oxygen_Bladder.description: A simple airtight vessel for storing extra oxygen.

Oxygen_Tank.description: A small tank for storing and consuming oxygen.
Oxygen_Tank.flavorText: While plants and animals were genetically adjusted to deal with the impurities in Icaruss air, humans need to bring their own.

Painting_Dark.description: A portrait painting on canvas with a charcoal frame.
Painting_Dark.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Painting_Gold.description: A large painting on canvas with a golden frame.
Painting_Gold.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Painting_Gold_Wood.description: A portrait painting on canvas with a gold leaf frame.
Painting_Gold_Wood.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Painting_Metal.description: A portrait painting on canvas with an iron frame.
Painting_Metal.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Painting_Scroll.description: A portrait painting on canvas held in a scroll.
Painting_Scroll.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Painting_Wood.description: A portrait painting on canvas with a wooden frame.
Painting_Wood.flavorText: Most artwork increases in value when the artist dies... the Icarus art trade must be booming.

Paints.description: Paints lovingly crafted for Portrait Painting

Paste_Food_Consumption.description: An organic confection that arrests hunger for a limited time.
Paste_Food_Consumption.flavorText: Just because its organic, doesnt mean its good for you.

Paste_Health_Buff.description: An organic preparation that temporarily increases health.
Paste_Health_Buff.flavorText: Like so many things on Icarus, the exact ingredients would probably render this concoction illegal on Earth.

Paste_Health_Regen.description: A herbal confection that speeds healing.
Paste_Health_Regen.flavorText: The lilys high concentration of bioactive ingredients is thought to inhibit the reuptake of certain cytochromes, briefly flooding your body with oxidating enzymes.

Paste_Health_Restore.description: An organic fusion that restores health.
Paste_Health_Restore.flavorText: The combination of Icaruss unique conditions and genetic adjustments to plant life has seen the addition of useful methyl chains to many previously innocuous plant-based preparations.

Paste_Oxygen_Buff.description: A natural concoction that increases available oxygen.
Paste_Oxygen_Buff.flavorText: Your parents are a long way from here. What you do with your body is your business.

Paste_Oxygen_Consumption.flavorText: This preparation reduces the heart rate, dropping oxygen consumption temporarily.

Paste_Oxygen_Restore.description: An organic co-factor that rapidly restores oxygen.

Paste_Stamina_Buff.description: A herbal concoction, temporarily increasing stamina.
Paste_Stamina_Buff.flavorText: While lacking some of the pharmaceutical refinements, this paste produces similar physiological affects to the wakers once offered to long haul space pilots.

Paste_Stamina_Consumption.description: A biotic compound that slows stamina loss temporarily.
Paste_Stamina_Consumption.flavorText: The time-jarring effects of exotics find their influence in many subtle, poorly understood ways on Icarus.

Paste_Stamina_Regen.description: An organic stimulant that accelerates stamina recovery.
Paste_Stamina_Regen.flavorText: A herbal preparation that acts rapidly on the sympathetic nervous system, increasing noradrenergic activity.

Paste_Stamina_Restore.description: A natural stimulant that restores lost stamina.
Paste_Stamina_Restore.flavorText: As countless athletes, party-goers and would-be mystics have noted, the line between natural stimulant and highly addictive narcotic is arbitrary, at best.

Paste_Water_Consumption.description: A natural preparation, temporarily reducing the bodys need for water.
Paste_Water_Consumption.flavorText: The key word here is temporarily.

Pastry.description: A simple but satisfying shortcrust pastry.
Pastry.flavorText: Icarus was only truly colonized when we began making pastry on that planet - Jacques Merrida

Pickaxe_Attachment_Copper_Yield_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to a valid pickaxe at an Alteration Bench.

Pickaxe_Attachment_Gold_Yield_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to a valid pickaxe at an Alteration Bench.

Pickaxe_Attachment_Platnium_Yield_2.flavorText: Can be equipped to a valid pickaxe at an Alteration Bench.

Pickled_Avocado.description: Avocado that has been marinated resulting in a tangy and slightly sour flavor.
Pickled_Avocado.flavorText: A handy snack made at your Kitchen Bench.

Pickled_Freshwater_Fillet.description: A tangy dish made by preserving tender fillets of freshwater fish in a flavorful mixture.
Pickled_Freshwater_Fillet.flavorText: Not for everyone, but a delicious long lasting treat for those that enjoy it.

Piranha_Statue_Wood.description: One of the fish of Icarus carved out of wood.

Platinum_Axe.description: An axceedingly reliable, accurate hewing tool.
Platinum_Axe.flavorText: Give me six hours to chop down a tree, Ill spend the first four sharpening the axe - A. Lincoln

Platinum_Bolt.flavorText: Though eclipsed by exotics, platinum remains extremely valuable, even if the market is somewhat distant.

Platinum_Crossbow.description: A crossbow that automatically reloads for rapid fire.
Platinum_Crossbow.flavorText: Its time for some serious damage.

Platinum_Hammer.description: Light, durable, accurate, but still a hammer.
Platinum_Hammer.flavorText: On Icarus, youre either the hammer, or the anvil - Javier Survez

Platinum_Ingot.description: An inert and corrosion-resistant metal, perfect for electronics.
Platinum_Ingot.flavorText: Enough platinum to found a small kingdom, were you on Earth.

Platinum_Knife.description: A precision blade, stronger than steel.
Platinum_Knife.flavorText: Platinums durablity gives an incredibly accurate, lethal cutting edge.

Platinum_Ore.description: As rare on Icarus as on Earth.
Platinum_Ore.flavorText: One of the least reactive metals in the universe, platinum requires extremely high temperatures for smelting and refinement.

Platinum_Pickaxe.flavorText: There is a small, but specific class of problems for which the only solution is a pickaxe.

Platinum_Shealth.description: A small sheath of platinum which can be used in a variety of electronics and machinery.

Platinum_Sickle.description: An extremely precise, high yield harvesting tool.
Platinum_Sickle.flavorText: A proletariat icon made from a near-priceless material, yet no more valuable than lead when compared to exotics themselves.

Platinum_Spear.description: Priceless on Earth. An advanced survival tool on Icarus.
Platinum_Spear.flavorText: A midweight, short-shafted ahlspeiss spear that, composition aside, would not have looked out of place in 16th century Prussia.

Platinum_Throwing_Knife.description: A precision blade, stronger than steel.
Platinum_Throwing_Knife.flavorText: Platinums durablity gives an incredibly accurate, lethal cutting edge.

Platinum_Throwing_Spear.description: Priceless on Earth. A projectile on Icarus.
Platinum_Throwing_Spear.flavorText: A midweight, short-shafted ahlspeiss spear that, composition aside, would not have looked out of place in 16th century Prussia.

Platinum_Weave.description: Platinum strands interwoven with a fiber based fabric.

Poison_Arrow.flavorText: Requiring less accuracy, but more patience, the poison arrow brings down quarry slowly, but surely.

Poison_Paste.description: A slow-working toxin made from spoiled meat.
Poison_Paste.flavorText: Life is a slow working poison - Jean Hurvit

Poison_Sack.description: A slightly squishy organ harvested from native creatures

Poison_Sack_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted from an intact poison sac.
Poison_Sack_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Poisoned_Bait.flavorText: Keep away from pets and children.

PolarBear_Armor_Head.flavorText: Once a warm high altitude desert, the arctics temperature dropped in the aftermath of failed terraforming, leaving a frigid wasteland of which the polar bear is now the unchallenged apex predator.

PolarBear_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Polar Bear.
PolarBear_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

PolarBear_Trophy.flavorText: Greater challenges await beyond the terrazone, but here, there is no greater emblem of your eminence.

Polarbear_Arms.description: Tough and lightweight fur gloves offering extreme protection against low temperatures.
Polarbear_Arms.flavorText: Skinning polar bears has been illegal to everyone except Inuit hunters for centuries on Earth. On Icarus, there is no such prohibition.

Polarbear_Chest.description: Strong, lightweight body armor with extreme protection against cold.
Polarbear_Chest.flavorText: Evolved for the most demanding climate on Earth, the polar bears skin works equally well in the most damaged environment on Icarus.

Polarbear_Feet.description: Highly insulated, lightweight protective fur boots.
Polarbear_Feet.flavorText: Evolved for the most demanding climate on Earth, the polar bears skin works equally well in the most damaged environment on Icarus.

Polarbear_Legs.description: Lightweight fur armor for the lower body, offering exceptional insulation.
Polarbear_Legs.flavorText: Once a warm high altitude desert, the arctics temperature dropped in the aftermath of failed terraforming, leaving a frigid wasteland of which the polar bear is now the unchallenged apex predator.

Polarbear_Pelt.description: A fur hide from the largest known carnivore on two planets.
Polarbear_Pelt.flavorText: An unparalleled hunter, able to smell its prey from over a mile away, the polar bear has only one natural enemy: you.

Portable_Beacon.description: Displays a map marker when deployed. Prospectors can adjust the map markers icon and colour by interacting with it.
Portable_Beacon.flavorText: Absorbs the smallest amount of light from any atmosphere and stores it in a small internal battery that can last for hundreds of years with minial charge. The beacon offers a BYO solution.

PotBellyStove.description: A wrought iron stove for cooking basic meals.
PotBellyStove.flavorText: Hearty and filling, the warm meals provided by this stove are the next steps towards culinary perfection.

Potato.description: A starchy tuber that makes up the base of many meals.
Potato.flavorText: Mash them, boil them, you can even put them in a stew.

Pronghorn_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Pronghorn.
Pronghorn_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Pronghorn_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

ProspectorID.description: The Standard ID of a Prospector Issued by the UDA

Prototype_Boss_Tracker.description: Certain large threats will be displayed on your map with this item if nearby.

Pumpkin.flavorText: Ensuring that Halloween becomes a multi-planet holiday. Best cooked.

Pygmy_Lop_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Pyritic_Crust_Bauxite.flavorText: The UDA has issued an Icarus-wide health warning regarding this material. Use at your own risk.

Rabbit_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Rabbit_Statue_Stone.description: Some rough stone carved into the shape of one of Icarus smallest creatures.
Rabbit_Statue_Stone.flavorText: The closest thing to a pet, for now.

Rabbit_Statue_Wood.description: A very rough carving of a rabbit.
Rabbit_Statue_Wood.flavorText: Looks similar to something made in shop class.

Rabbit_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Rabbit_Varient_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Pygmy Lop.
Rabbit_Varient_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Radar_Biofuel.description: A portable topographical radar unit powered by Biofuel. Nearby Local wildlife become agressive when this is active.
Radar_Biofuel.flavorText: Powered by good old Icarus Biofuel.

Radar_Electric.description: A portable topographical radar unit powered by Electricity, angers local wildlife when active.
Radar_Electric.flavorText: Connect this baby up to a generator and you are good to go.

Radar_Meta.description: Uses an internal power system to scan, though this does seem to attract a large amount of local wildlife when active.

Rain_Reservoir.description: A simple and durable way to collect rain water.
Rain_Reservoir.flavorText: Water can be consumed directly from the reservoir, or it will refill an equipped container.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_ADS_Upgrade_1.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid pistol, rifle, shotgun, bow, or crossbow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_ADS_Upgrade_2.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid pistol, rifle, shotgun, bow, or crossbow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Additional_Proj.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid crossbow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Lightweight_2.description: An attachment that increases your movement speed while aiming, and the amount you can carry.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Lightweight_2.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid pistol, shotgun, or rifle.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Rapid_Fire.description: An attachment that increases the speed of projectiles and your reload speed.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Rapid_Fire.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid bow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Sniper_1.description: An attachment that allows you a closer view of your target, and increases damage.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Sniper_1.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid rifle.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Sniper_2.description: An attachment that allows you an even closer view of your target, and greatly increases damage.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Sniper_2.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid rifle.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Speed_1.description: An attachment that increases your movement speed while aiming and your reload speed.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Speed_1.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid crossbow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Speed_2.description: An attachment that increases your movement speed while aiming and your reload speed.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Stealth_1.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid pistol, shotgun, or rifle.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Stealth_2.description: An attachment that greatly increases your damage while stealthed.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Stealth_2.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid pistol, shotgun, or rifle.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Wear_1.description: An attachment that increases the speed of projectiles and uses less stamina.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Wear_1.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid bow, or crossbow.

Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Wear_2.description: An attachment that greatly increases the speed of projectiles and uses less stamina.
Ranged_Weapon_Attachment_Wear_2.flavorText: Can be attached to a valid bow, or crossbow.

Raw_Fish.description: Will nourish, but better if cooked.
Raw_Fish.flavorText: Salmon and trout required only slight genetic adjustment to thrive in the waterways of Icarus.

Raw_Iron_Wood.description: A delicate substance often found coating creatures that inhabit swampy areas of Icarus.
Raw_Iron_Wood.flavorText: Exotics have been shown to warp and twist DNA on a molecular level, it would seem no living thing is safe.

Raw_Meat.description: Meat from a recently killed animal, worth cooking first.
Raw_Meat.flavorText: Transplanted from Earth, a range of genetically modified animals thrive in the terrazone, providing an energy-dense food source.

Raw_Prime_Meat.description: HIgh quality meat, though quick to spoil.
Raw_Prime_Meat.flavorText: The last word in Icarus cuisine, when properly cooked, though requires refrigeration soon after killing or will spoil.

Raw_Wood_Lamp.description: A charming lamp that emits a cozy glow.

Raw_Wood_Sign.description: A charming sign to display information on.

Raw_Wood_Sign_Trunk_A.description: A charming sign to display information on.

Raw_Wood_Sign_Trunk_B.description: A charming sign to display information on.

Reaver_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Reaver.
Reaver_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Recurve_Bow.description: With higher energy, recurve bows increase range and power.
Recurve_Bow.flavorText: Originating in ancient Scythia, the recurve bow stores energy more efficiently than a conventional bow, allowing for smaller, more compact weapons with an appreciable improvement in range and stopping power.

Redback_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Redback.
Redback_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Redback_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Reed_Flower.description: A wildflower reputed to have medicinal properties.
Reed_Flower.flavorText: Transplanting this reed to alien soil has altered its bioactive properties considerably.

Reed_Flower_Lure.description: A delicate lure carefully crafted out of flowers, to attract more fish.
Reed_Flower_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Refined_Copper.description: A pure ingot of copper, humanitys first metal.
Refined_Copper.flavorText: Easily worked, readily alloyed, a highly useful material for everything from weaponry to basic electronics.

Refined_Gold.flavorText: The existence of exotics on Icarus has demoted gold to the status of a useful, shiny metal.

Refined_Half_Pitch.flavorText: A two part construction element, containing a base slope and an upper slope, for building low-pitched roofs.

Refined_Halfpiece.description: Half- and quarter-sized building elements for detailed construction work.
Refined_Halfpiece.flavorText: These sets are useful for creating walkways, balconies, trims and a range of other smaller constructions.

Refined_Iron_Wood.description: A distilled essense of the Miasma that can be found on creatures in heavily exotic-affected areas.
Refined_Iron_Wood.flavorText: Exotics have been shown to warp and twist DNA on a molecular level, it would seem no living thing is safe.

Refined_Metal.flavorText: Iron may corode, but its ease of production makes it an ideal material on Icarus.

Refined_Wood_Fishing_Rod.description: A lightweight and reliable fishing rod.

Refined_Wood_Lure.description: A sophisticated lure carefully crafted out of wood, to attract more fish.
Refined_Wood_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Reinforced_Door.description: A heavy wooden door reinforced with iron bracing.
Reinforced_Door.flavorText: Once your structure has a doorway, this heavy door can be attached.

Reinforced_TrapDoor.description: A braced and bolstered wooden trapdoor.
Reinforced_TrapDoor.flavorText: May be attached to a floorpiece with a trapdoor accessway.

Reinforced_Window.description: A braced and bolstered wooden window.

Repair_Bench.description: Repairs any item, requiring power to repair tier 4 or workshop items.
Repair_Bench.flavorText: A little duct tape, maybe some lubricant, this bench can fix anything!

ResourceStack_Stone.flavorText: A time honored solution for storing rubble, stone and debris.

Rhubarb.description: A tart and tangy vegetable with large green leaves and pink or red stalks.
Rhubarb.flavorText: Rhubarb is a good source of vitamins C and K.

Rhubarb_Stew.flavorText: Another great meal from your Potbelly Stove.

Rifle_BoltAction.description: A single-shot bolt action, packs a punch.
Rifle_BoltAction.flavorText: Despite limited metallurgic and gunsmithing resources, First Cohort prospectors have managed to design a better-than-serviceable, true-aiming hunting rifle.

Rifle_Hunting.description: A semi-automatic rifle, ideal for big game hunting.
Rifle_Hunting.flavorText: An ancient hand-wrought weapon design, adapted to a new frontier.

Roat_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Roat.
Roat_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Roat_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Rope.description: Remains one of humanitys greatest inventions.
Rope.flavorText: A central element in crafting various construction materials and equipment.

Rotten_Meat_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted from... rotten meat.
Rotten_Meat_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Rubber_Lure.description: A basic lure carefully crafted out of rubber, to attract more fish.
Rubber_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Rug_Weave_Thick.description: A plainly woven, thick pile fiber mat.

Rug_Weave_Thin.flavorText: Four trillion kilometers from home, these details can make all the difference.

Rustic_Bed.description: An extra sturdy and comfortable bed.

Rustic_Bench.description: A rudimentary bench from which to watch the world go by.

Rustic_Bookshelf.description: A handmade bookshelf for more storage in your home.

Rustic_Cabinet.description: A simple cabinet for all of your collections.
Rustic_Cabinet.flavorText: Reducing clutter, one knicknack at a time.

Rustic_Candles.description: A cluster of candles, with four variations.

Rustic_CoffeeTable.description: A simple coffee table for your home.
Rustic_CoffeeTable.flavorText: Dont put a ring on it!

Rustic_CouchLarge.description: A large and cozy couch to share.
Rustic_CouchLarge.flavorText: Or to keep all for yourself.

Rustic_CouchMedium.flavorText: It could also just be a really big armchair.

Rustic_Decoration_Bench.description: A bench for crafting decorations from a range of tech levels.
Rustic_Decoration_Bench.flavorText: Pick up a new hobby, today!

Rustic_DiningChair.description: A basic dining chair for your home.

Rustic_Dresser.description: A simple dresser for all your bedroom needs.
Rustic_Dresser.flavorText: Would probably be worth a pretty penny back home.

Rustic_LivingChair.description: A comfortable armchair to relax in.
Rustic_LivingChair.flavorText: The perfect thing after a hard day of prospecting.

Rustic_NightStand.description: A basic nightstand to accompany your bed.
Rustic_NightStand.flavorText: Theres nothing better than a complete set.

Rustic_Pot.description: A simple pot to decorate your home.

Rustic_Statue.description: A statue commemorating the discovery of Icarus with two variations.

Rustic_Stool.flavorText: Perfect for reaching those higher shelves.

Rustic_TableLarge.flavorText: For when you want to throw a planetside dinner party.

Rustic_TableRound.flavorText: Perfect for planning a mission around.

Rustic_Wardrobe.description: An expansive wardrobe with three variations.
Rustic_Wardrobe.flavorText: The history of the wardrobe goes all the way back to the Romans.

Rustic_WardrobeNarrow.description: A narrower wardrobe for smaller homes, with two variations.
Rustic_WardrobeNarrow.flavorText: A smaller version but useful nonetheless.

Rustic_Wood_Shelf.flavorText: A shelf made of wood, your parents will be proud.

Saddle_Cart.description: Place this cart inside a tamed Buffalo or Tuskers inventory to greatly increase its carrying capacity. This cart cannot be used as a seat by players.
Saddle_Cart.flavorText: Lending a helping hand, or hoof.

Saddle_Standard.description: Place this saddle inside a tamed creatures inventory to allow it to become rideable
Saddle_Standard.flavorText: Feel the wind in your hair.

Saddle_Standard_Bag.description: Place this harness inside a tamed Buffalo or Tuskers inventory to increase its carrying capacity. This harness cannot be used as a seat by players.
Saddle_Standard_Bag.flavorText: Lending a helping hand, or hoof.

Salt.description: A small pile of Salt, can be used on a salting station to preserve food.
Salt.flavorText: An essential mineral for adding flavour and preserving food.

Salting_Station.description: Can be used to preserve food, using salt.

Saltwater_Fillet_Sashimi.description: A delicacy consisting of raw, thinly sliced saltwater fish.
Saltwater_Fillet_Sashimi.flavorText: Can be made at a Cooking Station. Simple, but delicious.

Saltwater_Fish_Fillet.description: A neatly trimmed fillet ready for cooking.

Sandworm_Arrow.flavorText: While the sandworms existence inside the terrazone is a mystery, its scales make extraordinarily practical blades.

Sandworm_Bow.description: A bow fashioned from the stronger scales of a Sandworm.

Sandworm_Knife.flavorText: Evolved to resist prolonged sand abrasion, the sandworms chitin-analogue scales holds an excellent edge.

Sandworm_Scale.flavorText: When held in the hand, fresh from the worms body, the scale gently vibrated. Slowly, this motion drained away, leaving only a flake of light, hugely strong armor.

Sandworm_Spear.description: A spear crafted from an ancient organisms armor.
Sandworm_Spear.flavorText: Group 15 continues to research sandworms, suspecting its subterranean evolution could hold clues to the bioeffects of exotics.

Sandworm_Throwing_Knife.flavorText: Evolved to resist prolonged sand abrasion, the sandworms chitin-analogue scales holds an excellent edge.

Sandworm_Throwing_Spear.description: A spear crafted from an ancient organisms armor.
Sandworm_Throwing_Spear.flavorText: Group 15 continues to research sandworms, suspecting its subterranean evolution could hold clues to the bioeffects of exotics.

Savory_Roll.description: A hearty pastry baked to perfection.
Savory_Roll.flavorText: A delicious meal made on your Biofuel Stove.

Scale_Arms.description: Provides decent all-round protection at the cost of aggravating nearby wildlife

Scale_Chest.description: Provides decent all-round protection at the cost of aggravating nearby wildlife

Scanner_Cave.description: A scanner that can locate caves within the surrounding area. Right click to toggle audible beeping.
Scanner_Cave.flavorText: Making life easier, one piece of technology at a time.

Scanner_DeepOre.description: A scanner that can locate various deep ore deposits within the surrounding area
Scanner_DeepOre.flavorText: A truly remarkable piece of equipment.

Scoria.description: A rough-textured rock ejected from the earth during volcanic activity.
Scoria.flavorText: Also known in some areas as lava stone.

Scoria_Beam.description: A beam that provides rustic style and function.
Scoria_Beam.flavorText: Not the most conventional building material but anything goes on Icarus.

Scoria_Brick.description: A basic building block for all Scoria Brick building pieces.
Scoria_Brick.flavorText: A pyroclastic, highly vesicular, dark-colored type of volcanic rock that has been ejected from the ground in a molten form and then cooled.

Scoria_Brick_Beam.description: A beam that provides both style and function.
Scoria_Brick_Beam.flavorText: The Scoria bricks used in this construction are far more lightweight than traditional building materials due to the trapped air pockets inside.

Scoria_Brick_Floor.flavorText: The Scoria bricks used in this construction are far more lightweight than traditional building materials due to the trapped air pockets inside.

Scoria_Brick_Halfpiece.description: A fancy half-piece for your walls.
Scoria_Brick_Halfpiece.flavorText: The Scoria bricks used in this construction are far more lightweight than traditional building materials due to the trapped air pockets inside.

Scoria_Brick_Ramp.description: A solid option for any construction.

Scorpian_Lure.description: A sophisticated lure carefully crafted out of a deadly Scorpion tail.
Scorpian_Lure.flavorText: Surely youll catch a big one with this in your kit.

Scorpion_Arms_Armor.description: Provides excellent protection at the cost of significantly aggravating nearby wildlife.
Scorpion_Arms_Armor.flavorText: No amount of washing will get rid of the smell.

Scorpion_Boss_Head.description: A preserved memory of a once-great Giant Scorpion.
Scorpion_Boss_Head.flavorText: Who knew taxidermy would be so popular on Icarus?

Scorpion_Boss_Trophy.flavorText: Evidence of skill, patience and accuracy.

Scorpion_Carapace.description: A remnant of a great beast.
Scorpion_Carapace.flavorText: A flake of light, but fairly strong armor.

Scorpion_Chest_Armor.description: Provides excellent protection at the cost of significantly aggravating nearby wildlife.
Scorpion_Chest_Armor.flavorText: No amount of washing will get rid of the smell.

Scorpion_Feet_Armor.description: Provides excellent protection at the cost of significantly aggravating nearby wildlife.

Scorpion_Head_Armor.description: Provides excellent protection at the cost of significantly aggravating nearby wildlife.
